Get title first title = soup.find('title') title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # CRITICAL FIX: Extract text content RIGHT HERE before using it print(f" Extracting text content...") full_text = soup.get_text() content_text_lower = full_text.lower() print(f" Text extracted - {len(full_text)} characters") # Now safely check for indicators education_indicators = ['tertiary', 'education', 'university', 'higher education', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'gender', 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female'] has_education_info = any(indicator in content_text_lower for indicator in education_indicators) census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'population', 'demographic', 'statistics'] has_census_info = any(indicator in content_text_lower for indicator in census_indicators) print(f" Education indicators found: {has_education_info}") print(f" Census indicators found: {has_census_info}") # Reconstruct URL from filename if 'censusresults' in filename: url = 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/' elif 'census2011' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/' elif '2011-population-census' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/2011-population-census' elif 'www_nsi_bg_en_' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/' else: url = 'Unknown source' priority_score = (has_education_info * 2) + (has_census_info * 2) successful_sources.append({ 'url': url, 'filename': filepath, 'title': title_text, 'has_education_info': has_education_info, 'has_census_info': has_census_info, 'content_length': len(html_content), 'priority_score': priority_score, 'full_text': full_text # Store for later analysis }) print(f" ‚úì Successfully analyzed - Priority score: {priority_score}") except Exception as e: print(f" ‚úó Error analyzing {filename}: {str(e)}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() # Sort sources by priority successful_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['priority_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== ANALYSIS RESULTS ===\n") print(f"Total sources successfully analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") if successful_sources: print("\n--- Sources Ranked by Relevance ---") for i, source in enumerate(successful_sources, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" Title: {source['title']}") print(f" Priority score: {source['priority_score']} (Education: {source['has_education_info']}, Census: {source['has_census_info']})") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print() # Deep dive into high-priority sources high_priority_sources = [s for s in successful_sources if s['priority_score'] >= 2] print(f"=== DETAILED CONTENT EXTRACTION ===\n") print(f"High-priority sources for detailed analysis: {len(high_priority_sources)}\n") all_tables_found = [] for source in high_priority_sources: print(f"DEEP ANALYSIS: {source['url']}") print(f"File: {source['filename']}") # Use the stored full_text to avoid re-parsing full_text = source['full_text'] # Re-parse for table extraction with open(source['filename'], 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Find tables and links tables = soup.find_all('table') links = soup.find_all('a') print(f"Found {len(tables)} tables and {len(links)} links") # Search for education and gender terms in both English and Bulgarian education_terms = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' # Bulgarian terms ] gender_terms = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'by sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' # Bulgarian terms ] content_lower = full_text.lower() found_education_terms = [term for term in education_terms if term.lower() in content_lower] found_gender_terms = [term for term in gender_terms if term.lower() in content_lower] print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}") # Look for statistical numbers number_pattern = r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b' numbers_found = re.findall(number_pattern, full_text) large_numbers = [num for num in numbers_found if len(num.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '')) >= 4] if large_numbers: print(f"Large numbers found (potential statistics): {large_numbers[:10]}...") # Show first 10 # Analyze tables for statistical data if tables: print(f"\nAnalyzing {len(tables)} tables for education/gender data...") for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text() table_text_lower = table_text.lower() # Check if table contains relevant content has_education = any(term.lower() in table_text_lower for term in education_terms) has_gender = any(term.lower() in table_text_lower for term in gender_terms) has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) # Numbers with 3+ digits if (has_education or has_gender) and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS RELEVANT DATA ***") rows = table.find_all('tr') print(f" Table has {len(rows)} rows") # Extract table structure table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: # Only add non-empty rows table_data.append(cells) if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0] if table_data else 'No headers'}") # Show sample data rows for j, row_data in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): if j < len(table_data) - 1: print(f" Row {j+1}: {row_data}") # Check for tertiary education indicators table_full_text = ' '.join([' '.join(row) for row in table_data]).lower() tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] has_tertiary = any(indicator in table_full_text for indicator in tertiary_indicators) if has_tertiary: print(f" *** TABLE CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") # Save relevant table table_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.json' table_info = { 'source_url': source['url'], 'source_title': source['title'], 'table_index': i, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'has_tertiary': has_tertiary, 'row_count': len(rows), 'table_data': table_data, 'found_education_terms': [term for term in education_terms if term.lower() in table_text_lower], 'found_gender_terms': [term for term in gender_terms if term.lower() in table_text_lower] } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) all_tables_found.append(table_info) print(f" Table saved to: {table_filename}") print(f" Table data saved to: {table_json_filename}") print("\n" + "="*80 + "\n") # Summary of findings print(f"=== EXTRACTION SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total census sources analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") print(f"High-priority sources: {len(high_priority_sources)}") print(f"Relevant tables containing education/gender data: {len(all_tables_found)}") if all_tables_found: print(f"\nTables with potential tertiary education data:") for i, table_info in enumerate(all_tables_found): print(f" Table {i+1}: {table_info['row_count']} rows, Source: {table_info['source_url']}") print(f" Has education: {table_info['has_education']}, Has gender: {table_info['has_gender']}, Has tertiary: {table_info['has_tertiary']}") print(f" Education terms: {table_info['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms: {table_info['found_gender_terms']}") print() else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education data found in initial analysis.") print("Will need to search for specific census publications or follow education-related links.") # Save comprehensive results final_results = { 'research_objective': '2011 Bulgarian Census - Tertiary Education by Gender', 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'sources_analyzed': len(successful_sources), 'high_priority_sources': len(high_priority_sources), 'relevant_tables_found': len(all_tables_found), 'sources_data': [{ 'url': s['url'], 'title': s['title'], 'has_education_info': s['has_education_info'], 'has_census_info': s['has_census_info'], 'priority_score': s['priority_score'], 'content_length': s['content_length'] } for s in successful_sources], # Don't store full_text in JSON 'tables_found': all_tables_found, 'status': 'Analysis completed successfully', 'next_steps': [ 'Analyze extracted tables for specific tertiary education numbers', 'Search for downloadable census reports or statistical publications', 'Follow education-related links for additional data sources', 'Look for gender-disaggregated tertiary education statistics' ] } with open('workspace/successful_census_analysis.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(final_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Final analysis results saved to: workspace/successful_census_analysis.json") print(f"Successfully analyzed {len(successful_sources)} census sources") print(f"Found {len(all_tables_found)} relevant tables saved as individual files") print(f"Next phase: Extract specific tertiary education statistics by gender from found tables") else: print("No sources were successfully analyzed. There may be an issue with the HTML files.")

Python Code python
import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER (VARIABLE ORDER FIXED) ===\n") print("Objective: Find gender breakdown of tertiary education completion in 2011 Bulgarian census") print("Target: Specific numbers for men and women with completed tertiary education\n") # Check what HTML files are available print("Checking workspace for census HTML files...") if os.path.exists('workspace'): all_files = os.listdir('workspace') html_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f"Found {len(html_files)} HTML files:") for file in html_files: file_path = os.path.join('workspace', file) file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") else: html_files = [] print() if not html_files: print("No HTML census files found. Need to download sources first.") exit() # Analyze HTML files with CORRECTLY ORDERED variable definitions print("=== ANALYZING CENSUS SOURCES FOR EDUCATION DATA ===\n") successful_sources = [] for filename in html_files: filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) print(f"Analyzing: {filename}") try: # Read the HTML file with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File read successfully - {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') print(f" HTML parsed successfully") # CRITICAL FIX: Define ALL text variables RIGHT HERE before using them full_text = soup.get_text() content_text_lower = full_text.lower() print(f" Text extracted - {len(full_text)} characters") # Get title title = soup.find('title') title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # NOW we can safely check for indicators using the properly defined variables education_indicators = ['tertiary', 'education', 'university', 'higher education', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'gender', 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female'] has_education_info = any(indicator in content_text_lower for indicator in education_indicators) census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'population', 'demographic', 'statistics'] has_census_info = any(indicator in content_text_lower for indicator in census_indicators) print(f" Education indicators found: {has_education_info}") print(f" Census indicators found: {has_census_info}") # Reconstruct URL from filename if 'censusresults' in filename: url = 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/' elif 'census2011' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/' elif '2011-population-census' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/2011-population-census' elif 'www_nsi_bg_en_' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/' else: url = 'Unknown source' priority_score = (has_education_info * 2) + (has_census_info * 2) successful_sources.append({ 'url': url, 'filename': filepath, 'title': title_text, 'has_education_info': has_education_info, 'has_census_info': has_census_info, 'content_length': len(html_content), 'priority_score': priority_score, 'full_text': full_text # Store for later analysis }) print(f" ‚úì Successfully analyzed - Priority score: {priority_score}") except Exception as e: print(f" ‚úó Error analyzing {filename}: {str(e)}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() # Sort sources by priority successful_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['priority_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== ANALYSIS RESULTS ===\n") print(f"Total sources successfully analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") if successful_sources: print("\n--- Sources Ranked by Relevance ---") for i, source in enumerate(successful_sources, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" Title: {source['title']}") print(f" Priority score: {source['priority_score']} (Education: {source['has_education_info']}, Census: {source['has_census_info']})") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print() # Deep dive into high-priority sources high_priority_sources = [s for s in successful_sources if s['priority_score'] >= 2] print(f"=== DETAILED CONTENT EXTRACTION ===\n") print(f"High-priority sources for detailed analysis: {len(high_priority_sources)}\n") all_tables_found = [] for source in high_priority_sources: print(f"DEEP ANALYSIS: {source['url']}") print(f"File: {source['filename']}") # Use the stored full_text to avoid re-parsing full_text = source['full_text'] # Re-parse for table extraction with open(source['filename'], 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Find tables and links tables = soup.find_all('table') links = soup.find_all('a') print(f"Found {len(tables)} tables and {len(links)} links") # Search for education and gender terms in both English and Bulgarian education_terms = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' # Bulgarian terms ] gender_terms = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'by sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' # Bulgarian terms ] content_lower = full_text.lower() found_education_terms = [term for term in education_terms if term.lower() in content_lower] found_gender_terms = [term for term in gender_terms if term.lower() in content_lower] print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}") # Look for statistical numbers number_pattern = r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b' numbers_found = re.findall(number_pattern, full_text) large_numbers = [num for num in numbers_found if len(num.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '')) >= 4] if large_numbers: print(f"Large numbers found (potential statistics): {large_numbers[:10]}...") # Show first 10 # Analyze tables for statistical data if tables: print(f"\nAnalyzing {len(tables)} tables for education/gender data...") for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text() table_text_lower = table_text.lower() # Check if table contains relevant content has_education = any(term.lower() in table_text_lower for term in education_terms) has_gender = any(term.lower() in table_text_lower for term in gender_terms) has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) # Numbers with 3+ digits if (has_education or has_gender) and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS RELEVANT DATA ***") rows = table.find_all('tr') print(f" Table has {len(rows)} rows") # Extract table structure table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: # Only add non-empty rows table_data.append(cells) if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0] if table_data else 'No headers'}") # Show sample data rows for j, row_data in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): if j + 1 < len(table_data): print(f" Row {j+1}: {row_data}") # Check for tertiary education indicators table_full_text = ' '.join([' '.join(row) for row in table_data]).lower() tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] has_tertiary = any(indicator in table_full_text for indicator in tertiary_indicators) if has_tertiary: print(f" *** TABLE CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") # Save relevant table table_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.json' table_info = { 'source_url': source['url'], 'source_title': source['title'], 'table_index': i, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'has_tertiary': has_tertiary, 'row_count': len(rows), 'table_data': table_data, 'found_education_terms': [term for term in education_terms if term.lower() in table_text_lower], 'found_gender_terms': [term for term in gender_terms if term.lower() in table_text_lower] } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) all_tables_found.append(table_info) print(f" Table saved to: {table_filename}") print(f" Table data saved to: {table_json_filename}") print("\n" + "="*80 + "\n") # Summary of findings print(f"=== EXTRACTION SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total census sources analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") print(f"High-priority sources: {len(high_priority_sources)}") print(f"Relevant tables containing education/gender data: {len(all_tables_found)}") if all_tables_found: print(f"\nTables with potential tertiary education data:") for i, table_info in enumerate(all_tables_found): print(f" Table {i+1}: {table_info['row_count']} rows, Source: {table_info['source_url']}") print(f" Has education: {table_info['has_education']}, Has gender: {table_info['has_gender']}, Has tertiary: {table_info['has_tertiary']}") print(f" Education terms: {table_info['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms: {table_info['found_gender_terms']}") print() else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education data found in initial analysis.") print("Will need to search for specific census publications or follow education-related links.") # Save comprehensive results final_results = { 'research_objective': '2011 Bulgarian Census - Tertiary Education by Gender', 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'sources_analyzed': len(successful_sources), 'high_priority_sources': len(high_priority_sources), 'relevant_tables_found': len(all_tables_found), 'sources_data': [{ 'url': s['url'], 'title': s['title'], 'has_education_info': s['has_education_info'], 'has_census_info': s['has_census_info'], 'priority_score': s['priority_score'], 'content_length': s['content_length'] } for s in successful_sources], # Don't store full_text in JSON 'tables_found': all_tables_found, 'status': 'Analysis completed successfully', 'next_steps': [ 'Analyze extracted tables for specific tertiary education numbers', 'Search for downloadable census reports or statistical publications', 'Follow education-related links for additional data sources', 'Look for gender-disaggregated tertiary education statistics' ] } with open('workspace/successful_census_analysis.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(final_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Final analysis results saved to: workspace/successful_census_analysis.json") print(f"Successfully analyzed {len(successful_sources)} census sources") print(f"Found {len(all_tables_found)} relevant tables saved as individual files") print(f"Next phase: Extract specific tertiary education statistics by gender from found tables") else: print("No sources were successfully analyzed. There may be an issue with the HTML files.")

Python Code python
import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER (SCOPING COMPLETELY FIXED) ===\n") print("Objective: Find gender breakdown of tertiary education completion in 2011 Bulgarian census") print("Target: Specific numbers for men and women with completed tertiary education\n") # Check what HTML files are available print("Checking workspace for census HTML files...") if os.path.exists('workspace'): all_files = os.listdir('workspace') html_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f"Found {len(html_files)} HTML files:") for file in html_files: file_path = os.path.join('workspace', file) file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") else: html_files = [] print() if not html_files: print("No HTML census files found. Need to download sources first.") exit() # Analyze HTML files with COMPLETELY RESTRUCTURED variable definitions print("=== ANALYZING CENSUS SOURCES FOR EDUCATION DATA ===\n") successful_sources = [] # Define education and census indicators OUTSIDE the loop to avoid scoping issues education_indicators = ['tertiary', 'education', 'university', 'higher education', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'gender', 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female'] census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'population', 'demographic', 'statistics'] for filename in html_files: filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) print(f"Analyzing: {filename}") try: # Read the HTML file with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File read successfully - {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') print(f" HTML parsed successfully") # Extract text content IMMEDIATELY after parsing full_text = soup.get_text() content_text_lower = full_text.lower() print(f" Text extracted - {len(full_text)} characters") # Get title title = soup.find('title') title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # NOW check for indicators using the properly defined content_text_lower has_education_info = any(indicator.lower() in content_text_lower for indicator in education_indicators) has_census_info = any(indicator.lower() in content_text_lower for indicator in census_indicators) print(f" Education indicators found: {has_education_info}") print(f" Census indicators found: {has_census_info}") # Reconstruct URL from filename if 'censusresults' in filename: url = 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/' elif 'census2011' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/' elif '2011-population-census' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/2011-population-census' elif 'www_nsi_bg_en_' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/' else: url = 'Unknown source' priority_score = (has_education_info * 2) + (has_census_info * 2) successful_sources.append({ 'url': url, 'filename': filepath, 'title': title_text, 'has_education_info': has_education_info, 'has_census_info': has_census_info, 'content_length': len(html_content), 'priority_score': priority_score, 'full_text': full_text # Store for later analysis }) print(f" ‚úì Successfully analyzed - Priority score: {priority_score}") except Exception as e: print(f" ‚úó Error analyzing {filename}: {str(e)}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() # Sort sources by priority successful_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['priority_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== ANALYSIS RESULTS ===\n") print(f"Total sources successfully analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") if successful_sources: print("\n--- Sources Ranked by Relevance ---") for i, source in enumerate(successful_sources, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" Title: {source['title']}") print(f" Priority score: {source['priority_score']} (Education: {source['has_education_info']}, Census: {source['has_census_info']})") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print() # Deep dive into high-priority sources high_priority_sources = [s for s in successful_sources if s['priority_score'] >= 2] print(f"=== DETAILED CONTENT EXTRACTION ===\n") print(f"High-priority sources for detailed analysis: {len(high_priority_sources)}\n") all_tables_found = [] for source in high_priority_sources: print(f"DEEP ANALYSIS: {source['url']}") print(f"File: {source['filename']}") # Use the stored full_text to avoid re-parsing full_text = source['full_text'] # Re-parse for table extraction with open(source['filename'], 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Find tables and links tables = soup.find_all('table') links = soup.find_all('a') print(f"Found {len(tables)} tables and {len(links)} links") # Search for education and gender terms in both English and Bulgarian education_terms = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' # Bulgarian terms ] gender_terms = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'by sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' # Bulgarian terms ] content_lower = full_text.lower() found_education_terms = [term for term in education_terms if term.lower() in content_lower] found_gender_terms = [term for term in gender_terms if term.lower() in content_lower] print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}") # Look for statistical numbers number_pattern = r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b' numbers_found = re.findall(number_pattern, full_text) large_numbers = [num for num in numbers_found if len(num.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '')) >= 4] if large_numbers: print(f"Large numbers found (potential statistics): {large_numbers[:10]}...") # Show first 10 # Analyze tables for statistical data if tables: print(f"\nAnalyzing {len(tables)} tables for education/gender data...") for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text() table_text_lower = table_text.lower() # Check if table contains relevant content has_education = any(term.lower() in table_text_lower for term in education_terms) has_gender = any(term.lower() in table_text_lower for term in gender_terms) has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) # Numbers with 3+ digits if (has_education or has_gender) and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS RELEVANT DATA ***") rows = table.find_all('tr') print(f" Table has {len(rows)} rows") # Extract table structure table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: # Only add non-empty rows table_data.append(cells) if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0] if table_data else 'No headers'}") # Show sample data rows for j, row_data in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): if j + 1 < len(table_data): print(f" Row {j+1}: {row_data}") # Check for tertiary education indicators table_full_text = ' '.join([' '.join(row) for row in table_data]).lower() tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] has_tertiary = any(indicator in table_full_text for indicator in tertiary_indicators) if has_tertiary: print(f" *** TABLE CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") # Save relevant table table_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.json' table_info = { 'source_url': source['url'], 'source_title': source['title'], 'table_index': i, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'has_tertiary': has_tertiary, 'row_count': len(rows), 'table_data': table_data, 'found_education_terms': [term for term in education_terms if term.lower() in table_text_lower], 'found_gender_terms': [term for term in gender_terms if term.lower() in table_text_lower] } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) all_tables_found.append(table_info) print(f" Table saved to: {table_filename}") print(f" Table data saved to: {table_json_filename}") print("\n" + "="*80 + "\n") # Summary of findings print(f"=== EXTRACTION SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total census sources analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") print(f"High-priority sources: {len(high_priority_sources)}") print(f"Relevant tables containing education/gender data: {len(all_tables_found)}") if all_tables_found: print(f"\nTables with potential tertiary education data:") for i, table_info in enumerate(all_tables_found): print(f" Table {i+1}: {table_info['row_count']} rows, Source: {table_info['source_url']}") print(f" Has education: {table_info['has_education']}, Has gender: {table_info['has_gender']}, Has tertiary: {table_info['has_tertiary']}") print(f" Education terms: {table_info['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms: {table_info['found_gender_terms']}") print() else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education data found in initial analysis.") print("Will need to search for specific census publications or follow education-related links.") # Save comprehensive results final_results = { 'research_objective': '2011 Bulgarian Census - Tertiary Education by Gender', 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'sources_analyzed': len(successful_sources), 'high_priority_sources': len(high_priority_sources), 'relevant_tables_found': len(all_tables_found), 'sources_data': [{ 'url': s['url'], 'title': s['title'], 'has_education_info': s['has_education_info'], 'has_census_info': s['has_census_info'], 'priority_score': s['priority_score'], 'content_length': s['content_length'] } for s in successful_sources], # Don't store full_text in JSON 'tables_found': all_tables_found, 'status': 'Analysis completed successfully', 'next_steps': [ 'Analyze extracted tables for specific tertiary education numbers', 'Search for downloadable census reports or statistical publications', 'Follow education-related links for additional data sources', 'Look for gender-disaggregated tertiary education statistics' ] } with open('workspace/successful_census_analysis.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(final_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Final analysis results saved to: workspace/successful_census_analysis.json") print(f"Successfully analyzed {len(successful_sources)} census sources") print(f"Found {len(all_tables_found)} relevant tables saved as individual files") print(f"Next phase: Extract specific tertiary education statistics by gender from found tables") else: print("No sources were successfully analyzed. There may be an issue with the HTML files.")

Summary of findings print(f"=== EXTRACTION SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total census sources analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") print(f"High-priority sources: {len(high_priority_sources)}") print(f"Relevant tables containing education/gender data: {len(all_tables_found)}") if all_tables_found: print(f"\nTables with potential tertiary education data:") for i, table_info in enumerate(all_tables_found): print(f" Table {i+1}: {table_info['row_count']} rows, Source: {table_info['source_url']}") print(f" Has education: {table_info['has_education']}, Has gender: {table_info['has_gender']}, Has tertiary: {table_info['has_tertiary']}") print(f" Education terms: {table_info['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms: {table_info['found_gender_terms']}") print() else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education data found in initial analysis.") print("Will need to search for specific census publications or follow education-related links.") # import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER (FINAL SCOPING FIX) ===\n") print("Objective: Find gender breakdown of tertiary education completion in 2011 Bulgarian census") print("Target: Specific numbers for men and women with completed tertiary education\n") # Check what HTML files are available print("Checking workspace for census HTML files...") if os.path.exists('workspace'): all_files = os.listdir('workspace') html_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f"Found {len(html_files)} HTML files:") for file in html_files: file_path = os.path.join('workspace', file) file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") else: html_files = [] print() if not html_files: print("No HTML census files found. Need to download sources first.") exit() # Analyze HTML files with COMPLETELY FIXED variable scoping print("=== ANALYZING CENSUS SOURCES FOR EDUCATION DATA ===\n") successful_sources = [] for filename in html_files: filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) print(f"Analyzing: {filename}") try: # Read the HTML file with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File read successfully - {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') print(f" HTML parsed successfully") # Extract text content IMMEDIATELY after parsing full_text = soup.get_text() content_text_lower = full_text.lower() print(f" Text extracted - {len(full_text)} characters") # Get title title = soup.find('title') title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # Define indicators as simple lists and check manually education_keywords = ['tertiary', 'education', 'university', 'higher education', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'gender', 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female'] census_keywords = ['2011', 'census', 'population', 'demographic', 'statistics'] # Check for education indicators has_education_info = False for keyword in education_keywords: if keyword.lower() in content_text_lower: has_education_info = True break # Check for census indicators has_census_info = False for keyword in census_keywords: if keyword.lower() in content_text_lower: has_census_info = True break print(f" Education indicators found: {has_education_info}") print(f" Census indicators found: {has_census_info}") # Reconstruct URL from filename if 'censusresults' in filename: url = 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/' elif 'census2011' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/' elif '2011-population-census' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/2011-population-census' elif 'www_nsi_bg_en_' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/' else: url = 'Unknown source' priority_score = (has_education_info * 2) + (has_census_info * 2) successful_sources.append({ 'url': url, 'filename': filepath, 'title': title_text, 'has_education_info': has_education_info, 'has_census_info': has_census_info, 'content_length': len(html_content), 'priority_score': priority_score, 'full_text': full_text # Store for later analysis }) print(f" ‚úì Successfully analyzed - Priority score: {priority_score}") except Exception as e: print(f" ‚úó Error analyzing {filename}: {str(e)}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() # Sort sources by priority successful_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['priority_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== ANALYSIS RESULTS ===\n") print(f"Total sources successfully analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") if successful_sources: print("\n--- Sources Ranked by Relevance ---") for i, source in enumerate(successful_sources, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" Title: {source['title']}") print(f" Priority score: {source['priority_score']} (Education: {source['has_education_info']}, Census: {source['has_census_info']})") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print() # Deep dive into high-priority sources high_priority_sources = [s for s in successful_sources if s['priority_score'] >= 2] print(f"=== DETAILED CONTENT EXTRACTION ===\n") print(f"High-priority sources for detailed analysis: {len(high_priority_sources)}\n") all_tables_found = [] for source in high_priority_sources: print(f"DEEP ANALYSIS: {source['url']}") print(f"File: {source['filename']}") # Use the stored full_text to avoid re-parsing full_text = source['full_text'] # Re-parse for table extraction with open(source['filename'], 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Find tables and links tables = soup.find_all('table') links = soup.find_all('a') print(f"Found {len(tables)} tables and {len(links)} links") # Search for education and gender terms in both English and Bulgarian education_terms = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' # Bulgarian terms ] gender_terms = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'by sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' # Bulgarian terms ] content_lower = full_text.lower() found_education_terms = [] found_gender_terms = [] # Check for education terms for term in education_terms: if term.lower() in content_lower: found_education_terms.append(term) # Check for gender terms for term in gender_terms: if term.lower() in content_lower: found_gender_terms.append(term) print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}") # Look for statistical numbers number_pattern = r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b' numbers_found = re.findall(number_pattern, full_text) large_numbers = [num for num in numbers_found if len(num.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '')) >= 4] if large_numbers: print(f"Large numbers found (potential statistics): {large_numbers[:10]}...") # Show first 10 # Analyze tables for statistical data if tables: print(f"\nAnalyzing {len(tables)} tables for education/gender data...") for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text() table_text_lower = table_text.lower() # Check if table contains relevant content has_education = False for term in education_terms: if term.lower() in table_text_lower: has_education = True break has_gender = False for term in gender_terms: if term.lower() in table_text_lower: has_gender = True break has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) # Numbers with 3+ digits if (has_education or has_gender) and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS RELEVANT DATA ***") rows = table.find_all('tr') print(f" Table has {len(rows)} rows") # Extract table structure table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: # Only add non-empty rows table_data.append(cells) if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0] if table_data else 'No headers'}") # Show sample data rows for j, row_data in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): if j + 1 < len(table_data): print(f" Row {j+1}: {row_data}") # Check for tertiary education indicators table_full_text = ' '.join([' '.join(row) for row in table_data]).lower() tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] has_tertiary = False for indicator in tertiary_indicators: if indicator in table_full_text: has_tertiary = True break if has_tertiary: print(f" *** TABLE CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") # Save relevant table table_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/relevant_table_{len(all_tables_found)}.json' # Find education and gender terms in this specific table table_education_terms = [] table_gender_terms = [] for term in education_terms: if term.lower() in table_text_lower: table_education_terms.append(term) for term in gender_terms: if term.lower() in table_text_lower: table_gender_terms.append(term) table_info = { 'source_url': source['url'], 'source_title': source['title'], 'table_index': i, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'has_tertiary': has_tertiary, 'row_count': len(rows), 'table_data': table_data, 'found_education_terms': table_education_terms, 'found_gender_terms': table_gender_terms } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) all_tables_found.append(table_info) print(f" Table saved to: {table_filename}") print(f" Table data saved to: {table_json_filename}") print("\n" + "="*80 + "\n") # Summary of findings print(f"=== EXTRACTION SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total census sources analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") print(f"High-priority sources: {len(high_priority_sources)}") print(f"Relevant tables containing education/gender data: {len(all_tables_found)}") if all_tables_found: print(f"\nTables with potential tertiary education data:") for i, table_info in enumerate(all_tables_found): print(f" Table {i+1}: {table_info['row_count']} rows, Source: {table_info['source_url']}") print(f" Has education: {table_info['has_education']}, Has gender: {table_info['has_gender']}, Has tertiary: {table_info['has_tertiary']}") print(f" Education terms: {table_info['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms: {table_info['found_gender_terms']}") print() else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education data found in initial analysis.") print("Will need to search for specific census publications or follow education-related links.") # Save comprehensive results final_results = { 'research_objective': '2011 Bulgarian Census - Tertiary Education by Gender', 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'sources_analyzed': len(successful_sources), 'high_priority_sources': len(high_priority_sources), 'relevant_tables_found': len(all_tables_found), 'sources_data': [{ 'url': s['url'], 'title': s['title'], 'has_education_info': s['has_education_info'], 'has_census_info': s['has_census_info'], 'priority_score': s['priority_score'], 'content_length': s['content_length'] } for s in successful_sources], # Don't store full_text in JSON 'tables_found': all_tables_found, 'status': 'Analysis completed successfully', 'next_steps': [ 'Analyze extracted tables for specific tertiary education numbers', 'Search for downloadable census reports or statistical publications', 'Follow education-related links for additional data sources', 'Look for gender-disaggregated tertiary education statistics' ] } with open('workspace/successful_census_analysis.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(final_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Final analysis results saved to: workspace/successful_census_analysis.json") print(f"Successfully analyzed {len(successful_sources)} census sources") print(f"Found {len(all_tables_found)} relevant tables saved as individual files") print(f"Next phase: Extract specific tertiary education statistics by gender from found tables") else: print("No sources were successfully analyzed. There may be an issue with the HTML files.")

Reconstruct URL from filename if 'censusresults' in filename: url = 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/' elif 'census2011' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/' elif '2011-population-census' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/2011-population-census' elif 'www_nsi_bg_en_' in filename: url = 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/' else: url = 'Unknown source' priority_score = (has_education_info * 2) + (has_census_info * 2) successful_sources.append({ 'url': url, 'filename': filepath, 'title': title_text, 'has_education_info': has_education_info, 'has_census_info': has_census_info, 'content_length': len(html_content), 'priority_score': priority_score, 'full_text': full_text # Store for later analysis }) print(f" ‚úì Successfully analyzed - Priority score: {priority_score}") except Exception as e: print(f" ‚úó Error analyzing {filename}: {str(e)}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() # Sort sources by priority successful_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['priority_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== ANALYSIS RESULTS ===\n") print(f"Total sources successfully analyzed: {len(successful_sources)}") if successful_sources: print("\n--- Sources Ranked by Relevance ---") for i, source in enumerate(successful_sources, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" Title: {source['title']}") print(f" Priority score: {source['priority_score']} (Education: {source['has_education_info']}, Census: {source['has_census_info']})") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print() # Deep dive into high-priority sources high_priority_sources = [s for s in successful_sources if s['priority_score'] >= 2] print(f"=== DETAILED CONTENT EXTRACTION ===\n") print(f"High-priority sources for detailed analysis: {len(high_priority_sources)}\n") all_tables_found = [] for source in high_priority_sources: print(f"DEEP ANALYSIS: {source['url']}") print(f"File: {source['filename']}") # Use the stored full_text to avoid re-parsing full_text = source['full_text'] # Re-parse for table extraction with open(source['filename'], 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Find tables and links tables = soup.find_all('table') links = soup.find_all('a') print(f"Found {len(tables)} tables and {len(links)} links") # Search for education and gender terms in both English and Bulgarian education_terms = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' # Bulgarian terms ] gender_terms = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'by sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' # Bulgarian terms ] content_lower = full_text.lower() found_education_terms = [] found_gender_terms = [] # Look for statistical numbers number_pattern = r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b' numbers_found = re.findall(number_pattern, full_text) large_numbers = [num for num in numbers_found if len(num.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '')) >= 4] if large_numbers: print(f"Large numbers found (potential statistics): {large_numbers[:10]}...") # import os import json import requests print("=== SEARCHING FOR 2011 BULGARIAN CENSUS TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ===\n") print("Objective: Find official census publications with gender breakdown of tertiary education") print("Target: Specific numbers for men and women with completed tertiary education\n") # Get SerpAPI key from environment variables api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key is None: print("Error: Missing API key. Make sure you have SERPAPI_API_KEY in your environment variables.") exit() # Search queries targeting Bulgarian census education statistics search_queries = [ '"2011 Bulgarian census" "tertiary education" gender statistics men women', 'Bulgaria census 2011 "higher education" "by sex" statistics NSI', '"Bulgarian National Statistical Institute" 2011 census education gender breakdown', 'site:nsi.bg 2011 census tertiary education men women statistics', '"–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ" "–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª" 2011 –ø—Ä–µ–±—Ä–æ—è–≤–∞–Ω–µ –ë—ä–ª–≥–∞—Ä–∏—è —Å—Ç–∞—Ç–∏—Å—Ç–∏–∫–∞', # Bulgarian terms 'Bulgaria 2011 population census education attainment gender disaggregated data' ] print("Executing targeted searches for Bulgarian census education data...\n") all_search_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f"Search {i}/6: {query}") # Prepare API request parameters params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10, "type": "search" } try: # Make API request to SerpAPI response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f" Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results") # Extract relevant results for result in results["organic_results"]: title = result.get('title', '') link = result.get('link', '') snippet = result.get('snippet', '') # Check for relevance indicators relevance_keywords = ['census', '2011', 'education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'gender', 'men', 'women', 'statistics', 'nsi.bg'] relevance_score = sum(1 for keyword in relevance_keywords if keyword.lower() in (title + snippet + link).lower()) if relevance_score >= 3: # Must have at least 3 relevant keywords all_search_results.append({ 'query': query, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) print(f" ‚úì Relevant: {title[:60]}... (Score: {relevance_score})") else: print(" No results found") else: print(f" Error: API request failed with status {response.status_code}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error: {str(e)}") print() # Sort results by relevance score all_search_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total relevant results found: {len(all_search_results)}") if all_search_results: print("\n--- Top Results by Relevance ---") # Show top 10 most relevant results for i, result in enumerate(all_search_results[:10], 1): print(f"{i}. {result['title']}") print(f" URL: {result['link']}") print(f" Relevance Score: {result['relevance_score']}") print(f" Snippet: {result['snippet'][:100]}...") print() # Look for official NSI sources nsi_results = [r for r in all_search_results if 'nsi.bg' in r['link']] print(f"Official NSI sources found: {len(nsi_results)}") # Look for PDF documents (likely to contain detailed statistics) pdf_results = [r for r in all_search_results if '.pdf' in r['link'].lower()] print(f"PDF documents found: {len(pdf_results)}") # Look for results mentioning specific numbers or statistics statistical_results = [r for r in all_search_results if any(term in (r['title'] + r['snippet']).lower() for term in ['%', 'percent', 'thousand', 'million', 'statistics', 'data'])] print(f"Results with statistical indicators: {len(statistical_results)}") # Priority sources for download priority_sources = [] # Prioritize official NSI sources for result in nsi_results: if result['relevance_score'] >= 4: priority_sources.append(result) # Add high-relevance PDF sources for result in pdf_results: if result['relevance_score'] >= 5 and result not in priority_sources: priority_sources.append(result) # Add other high-relevance sources for result in all_search_results: if result['relevance_score'] >= 6 and result not in priority_sources: priority_sources.append(result) print(f"\n=== PRIORITY SOURCES FOR ANALYSIS ===\n") print(f"Identified {len(priority_sources)} priority sources") if priority_sources: for i, source in enumerate(priority_sources, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['title']}") print(f" URL: {source['link']}") print(f" Relevance: {source['relevance_score']}") print(f" Description: {source['snippet'][:150]}...") # Check for specific education/gender indicators in snippet snippet_lower = source['snippet'].lower() education_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher education', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'by sex'] found_education = [ind for ind in education_indicators if ind in snippet_lower] found_gender = [ind for ind in gender_indicators if ind in snippet_lower] if found_education or found_gender: print(f" Key terms: Education: {found_education}, Gender: {found_gender}") print() # Save comprehensive search results search_summary = { 'search_objective': '2011 Bulgarian Census - Tertiary Education by Gender', 'search_timestamp': '2024-12-19', 'total_queries_executed': len(search_queries), 'total_relevant_results': len(all_search_results), 'nsi_official_sources': len(nsi_results), 'pdf_documents_found': len(pdf_results), 'statistical_results': len(statistical_results), 'priority_sources_identified': len(priority_sources), 'search_queries_used': search_queries, 'all_results': all_search_results, 'priority_sources': priority_sources, 'next_steps': [ 'Download and analyze priority sources', 'Extract specific tertiary education statistics by gender', 'Look for official census publications with detailed breakdowns', 'Search for NSI statistical yearbooks or education reports' ] } with open('workspace/census_search_results.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(search_summary, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"=== SEARCH COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Search results saved to: workspace/census_search_results.json") print(f"Found {len(all_search_results)} relevant sources across {len(search_queries)} targeted searches") print(f"Identified {len(priority_sources)} high-priority sources for detailed analysis") print(f"Next step: Download and analyze priority sources for specific tertiary education statistics") else: print("No relevant results found. May need to adjust search terms or try alternative approaches.") print("Consider searching for:") print("- Bulgarian National Statistical Institute annual reports") print("- European statistical databases (Eurostat)") print("- Academic papers citing Bulgarian education statistics") print("- International education databases")

import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import os import json import time print("=== DIRECT ACCESS TO BULGARIAN NSI FOR 2011 CENSUS EDUCATION DATA ===\n") print("Objective: Access official NSI publications for tertiary education by gender") print("Target: Find specific numbers for men and women with completed tertiary education\n") # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } # Target specific NSI URLs for census education data target_urls = [ 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/education-2011-census', 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/population-education', 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/educational-attainment-population', 'https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/PDOCS2/Census2011final_en.pdf', 'https://www.nsi.bg/sites/default/files/files/publications/Census2011final_en.pdf', 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/Census/Reports/2/2/R4.aspx', 'https://censusresults.nsi.bg/Census/Reports/2/2/R3.aspx', 'https://www.nsi.bg/en/content/2011-population-and-housing-census-main-results', 'https://www.nsi.bg/sites/default/files/files/data/timeseries/Education_1.1.xls', 'https://www.nsi.bg/sites/default/files/files/data/timeseries/Education_1.2.xls' ] successful_downloads = [] failed_downloads = [] print("Attempting to access NSI education and census resources...\n") for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"Accessing {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f" Status: {response.status_code}") if response.status_code == 200: content_type = response.headers.get('content-type', '').lower() content_length = len(response.content) print(f" Content type: {content_type}") print(f" Content length: {content_length} bytes") # Determine file extension based on content type and URL if '.pdf' in url.lower() or 'pdf' in content_type: file_ext = '.pdf' elif '.xls' in url.lower() or 'excel' in content_type or 'spreadsheet' in content_type: file_ext = '.xls' elif 'html' in content_type or 'text' in content_type: file_ext = '.html' else: file_ext = '.html' # Default to HTML # Create filename filename = f"nsi_education_source_{i}{file_ext}" filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) # Save content with open(filepath, 'wb') as f: f.write(response.content) # Analyze content for education/gender indicators if file_ext == '.html': try: soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') text_content = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for education terms education_terms = ['tertiary', 'higher education', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', 'education level'] gender_terms = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'by sex', 'gender'] found_education = [term for term in education_terms if term in text_content] found_gender = [term for term in gender_terms if term in text_content] # Look for statistical tables tables = soup.find_all('table') print(f" ‚úì HTML analyzed: {len(tables)} tables, Education terms: {found_education}, Gender terms: {found_gender}") except Exception as e: print(f" HTML analysis error: {str(e)}") found_education = [] found_gender = [] tables = [] else: found_education = ['Unknown - binary file'] found_gender = ['Unknown - binary file'] tables = [] successful_downloads.append({ 'url': url, 'filename': filepath, 'content_type': content_type, 'content_length': content_length, 'file_extension': file_ext, 'found_education_terms': found_education, 'found_gender_terms': found_gender, 'table_count': len(tables) if isinstance(tables, list) else 0 }) print(f" ‚úì Saved as: {filename}") else: failed_downloads.append({'url': url, 'status_code': response.status_code}) print(f" ‚úó Failed with status {response.status_code}") except Exception as e: failed_downloads.append({'url': url, 'error': str(e)}) print(f" ‚úó Error: {str(e)}") print() time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to the server print(f"=== DOWNLOAD RESULTS ===\n") print(f"Successful downloads: {len(successful_downloads)}") print(f"Failed downloads: {len(failed_downloads)}") if successful_downloads: print("\n--- Successfully Downloaded Sources ---") for i, source in enumerate(successful_downloads, 1): print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print(f" Type: {source['content_type']} ({source['content_length']} bytes)") print(f" Education terms: {source['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms: {source['found_gender_terms']}") if source['table_count'] > 0: print(f" Tables found: {source['table_count']}") print() # Prioritize sources with both education and gender indicators priority_sources = [] for source in successful_downloads: has_education = len(source['found_education_terms']) > 0 and 'Unknown' not in str(source['found_education_terms']) has_gender = len(source['found_gender_terms']) > 0 and 'Unknown' not in str(source['found_gender_terms']) has_tables = source['table_count'] > 0 priority_score = (has_education * 2) + (has_gender * 2) + (has_tables * 1) if priority_score >= 3: # Must have good indicators priority_sources.append({ 'source': source, 'priority_score': priority_score, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'has_tables': has_tables }) priority_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['priority_score'], reverse=True) print(f"=== HIGH-PRIORITY SOURCES FOR ANALYSIS ===\n") print(f"Sources with strong education/gender indicators: {len(priority_sources)}\n") if priority_sources: for i, ps in enumerate(priority_sources, 1): source = ps['source'] print(f"{i}. {source['url']}") print(f" Priority Score: {ps['priority_score']} (Education: {ps['has_education']}, Gender: {ps['has_gender']}, Tables: {ps['has_tables']})") print(f" File: {source['filename']}") print(f" Education terms found: {source['found_education_terms']}") print(f" Gender terms found: {source['found_gender_terms']}") print() # Analyze the highest priority source in detail top_source = priority_sources[0]['source'] print(f"=== DETAILED ANALYSIS OF TOP SOURCE ===\n") print(f"Analyzing: {top_source['url']}") print(f"File: {top_source['filename']}\n") if top_source['file_extension'] == '.html': try: with open(top_source['filename'], 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Look for tables with education data tables = soup.find_all('table') print(f"Found {len(tables)} tables to analyze...\n") relevant_tables = [] for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text().lower() # Check for tertiary education indicators tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'by sex'] has_tertiary = any(indicator in table_text for indicator in tertiary_indicators) has_gender_data = any(indicator in table_text for indicator in gender_indicators) has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) # Numbers with 3+ digits if has_tertiary and has_gender_data and has_numbers: print(f"*** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER DATA ***") # Extract table data rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f"Table has {len(table_data)} rows") if table_data: print(f"Headers: {table_data[0]}") for j, row in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): print(f"Row {j+1}: {row}") # Save this table table_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_table_{len(relevant_tables)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_table_{len(relevant_tables)}.json' table_info = { 'source_url': top_source['url'], 'table_index': i, 'has_tertiary': has_tertiary, 'has_gender_data': has_gender_data, 'has_numbers': has_numbers, 'row_count': len(table_data), 'table_data': table_data } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) relevant_tables.append(table_info) print(f"Table saved to: {table_filename}") print(f"Table data saved to: {table_json_filename}") print() print(f"Found {len(relevant_tables)} tables with tertiary education by gender data") except Exception as e: print(f"Error analyzing top source: {str(e)}") else: print(f"Top source is a {top_source['file_extension']} file - requires specialized analysis") else: print("No sources found with strong education and gender indicators.") print("Will analyze all downloaded sources for any relevant data.") # Save comprehensive download summary download_summary = { 'objective': '2011 Bulgarian Census - Tertiary Education by Gender', 'download_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'urls_attempted': len(target_urls), 'successful_downloads': len(successful_downloads), 'failed_downloads': len(failed_downloads), 'priority_sources_identified': len(priority_sources) if 'priority_sources' in locals() else 0, 'sources_downloaded': successful_downloads, 'failed_attempts': failed_downloads, 'status': 'Download phase completed', 'next_steps': [ 'Analyze downloaded files for specific tertiary education statistics', 'Extract gender-disaggregated numbers for tertiary education completion', 'Process PDF and Excel files if downloaded', 'Search for official census tables with education breakdowns' ] } with open('workspace/nsi_download_summary.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(download_summary, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n=== DOWNLOAD PHASE COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Download summary saved to: workspace/nsi_download_summary.json") print(f"Successfully downloaded {len(successful_downloads)} sources from NSI") if 'priority_sources' in locals(): print(f"Identified {len(priority_sources)} high-priority sources for analysis") print(f"Next step: Analyze downloaded content for specific tertiary education statistics by gender")

Save this table table_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_table_{len(relevant_tables)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_table_{len(relevant_tables)}.json' table_info = { 'source_url': top_source['url'], 'table_index': i, 'has_tertiary': has_tertiary, 'has_gender_data': has_gender_data, 'has_numbers': has_numbers, 'row_count': len(table_data), 'table_data': table_data } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) relevant_tables.append(table_info) print(f"Table saved to: {table_filename}") print(f"Table data saved to: {table_json_filename}") print() print(f"Found {len(relevant_tables)} tables with tertiary education by gender data") except Exception as e: print(f"Error analyzing top source: {str(e)}") else: print(f"Top source is a {top_source['file_extension']} file - requires specialized analysis") else: print("No sources found with strong education and gender indicators.") print("Will analyze all downloaded sources for any relevant data.") # Python Code python
import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER DATA EXTRACTION ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Find gender-disaggregated statistics from 2011 Bulgarian census\n") # Check workspace for available files workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for census-related files...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) print(f"Found {len(all_files)} files in workspace:") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print() # Look for JSON analysis files that might contain structured census data json_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.json')] html_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f"JSON files for analysis: {len(json_files)}") print(f"HTML files for analysis: {len(html_files)}\n") # First, let's inspect any JSON files to understand their structure if json_files: print("=== INSPECTING JSON FILES FOR CENSUS DATA ===\n") for json_file in json_files: print(f"Inspecting: {json_file}") json_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, json_file) try: with open(json_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(content)} characters") # Parse JSON to understand structure try: json_data = json.loads(content) print(f" JSON type: {type(json_data)}") if isinstance(json_data, dict): print(f" Top-level keys: {list(json_data.keys())[:10]}") # Look for census or education-related keys census_keywords = ['census', 'education', 'tertiary', 'gender', 'men', 'women', 'statistics', 'population'] relevant_keys = [] for key in json_data.keys(): key_lower = str(key).lower() if any(keyword in key_lower for keyword in census_keywords): relevant_keys.append(key) if relevant_keys: print(f" *** RELEVANT KEYS FOUND: {relevant_keys} ***") # Examine relevant sections for key in relevant_keys[:3]: # Look at first 3 relevant keys value = json_data[key] print(f" {key}: {type(value)}") if isinstance(value, list) and len(value) > 0: print(f" List length: {len(value)}") print(f" First item: {value[0]}") elif isinstance(value, dict): print(f" Dict keys: {list(value.keys())[:5]}") else: print(f" Value: {str(value)[:100]}...") # Search for specific education/gender terms in the entire JSON json_str = json.dumps(json_data).lower() education_terms = ['tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master'] gender_terms = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'by sex', 'gender'] found_education = [term for term in education_terms if term in json_str] found_gender = [term for term in gender_terms if term in json_str] if found_education or found_gender: print(f" *** CONTAINS TARGET TERMS ***") print(f" Education terms: {found_education}") print(f" Gender terms: {found_gender}") # Look for numerical data that could be statistics numbers = re.findall(r'\b\d{3,}\b', json_str) if numbers: print(f" Large numbers found: {numbers[:10]}...") elif isinstance(json_data, list): print(f" JSON list length: {len(json_data)}") if len(json_data) > 0: print(f" First item type: {type(json_data[0])}") if isinstance(json_data[0], dict): print(f" First item keys: {list(json_data[0].keys())[:5]}") except json.JSONDecodeError as e: print(f" JSON parsing error: {e}") print(f" Content preview: {content[:200]}...") except Exception as e: print(f" Error reading file: {e}") print() # Now let's look at HTML files for census tables if html_files: print("=== ANALYZING HTML FILES FOR CENSUS TABLES ===\n") for html_file in html_files: print(f"Analyzing: {html_file}") html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Get title title = soup.find('title') title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # Extract text content text_content = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for Bulgarian census and education indicators census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'recensƒÉm√¢nt', '–ø—Ä–µ–±—Ä–æ—è–≤–∞–Ω–µ', 'population', '–Ω–∞—Å–µ–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ'] education_indicators = ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–ø–æ–ª'] found_census = [ind for ind in census_indicators if ind in text_content] found_education = [ind for ind in education_indicators if ind in text_content] found_gender = [ind for ind in gender_indicators if ind in text_content] print(f" Census indicators: {found_census}") print(f" Education indicators: {found_education}") print(f" Gender indicators: {found_gender}") # Look for tables tables = soup.find_all('table') print(f" Tables found: {len(tables)}") if tables and (found_education or found_gender): print(f" *** ANALYZING {len(tables)} TABLES FOR EDUCATION DATA ***") for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text().lower() # Check if table contains education and gender data has_education = any(term in table_text for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']) has_gender = any(term in table_text for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']) has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) if has_education and has_gender and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS EDUCATION + GENDER + STATISTICS ***") # Extract table structure rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f" Rows: {len(table_data)}") if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0]}") # Show first few data rows for j, row in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): if j + 1 < len(table_data): print(f" Row {j+1}: {row}") # Look for tertiary education specifically table_full_text = ' '.join([' '.join(row) for row in table_data]).lower() # Search for tertiary education patterns tertiary_patterns = [ 'tertiary', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω' ] found_tertiary = [pattern for pattern in tertiary_patterns if pattern in table_full_text] if found_tertiary: print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION INDICATORS: {found_tertiary} ***") # Try to extract specific numbers # Look for rows with gender and numbers for k, row in enumerate(table_data): row_text = ' '.join(row).lower() # Check if row contains gender terms and numbers has_men = any(term in row_text for term in ['men', 'male', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏']) has_women = any(term in row_text for term in ['women', 'female', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏']) numbers_in_row = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', ' '.join(row)) if (has_men or has_women) and numbers_in_row: print(f" *** POTENTIAL GENDER DATA ROW {k}: {row} ***") print(f" Numbers found: {numbers_in_row}") # Save this important table table_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{i}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{i}.json' table_info = { 'source_file': html_file, 'table_index': i, 'has_tertiary_education': bool(found_tertiary), 'tertiary_indicators': found_tertiary, 'row_count': len(table_data), 'table_data': table_data, 'extraction_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f" Table saved: {table_filename}") print(f" Data saved: {table_json_filename}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error analyzing HTML file: {e}") print() print("=== SUMMARY OF ANALYSIS ===\n") print(f"Workspace files analyzed: {len(all_files)}") print(f"JSON files inspected: {len(json_files)}") print(f"HTML files analyzed: {len(html_files)}") # Check if we found any tertiary education tables tertiary_tables = [f for f in os.listdir(workspace_path) if 'tertiary_education_gender_table' in f and f.endswith('.json')] if tertiary_tables: print(f"\n*** FOUND {len(tertiary_tables)} TABLES WITH TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") print("\nNext step: Extract specific numbers for men and women from these tables") else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education by gender data found.") print("May need to search for official NSI statistical publications or census reports.") print(f"\nAnalysis complete. Check workspace for extracted table files.")

Parse HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Get title title = soup.find('title') title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # Extract text content text_content = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for Bulgarian census and education indicators census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'recensƒÉm√¢nt', '–ø—Ä–µ–±—Ä–æ—è–≤–∞–Ω–µ', 'population', '–Ω–∞—Å–µ–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ'] education_indicators = ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–ø–æ–ª'] found_census = [ind for ind in census_indicators if ind in text_content] found_education = [ind for ind in education_indicators if ind in text_content] found_gender = [ind for ind in gender_indicators if ind in text_content] print(f" Census indicators: {found_census}") print(f" Education indicators: {found_education}") print(f" Gender indicators: {found_gender}") # Look for tables tables = soup.find_all('table') print(f" Tables found: {len(tables)}") if tables and (found_education or found_gender): print(f" *** ANALYZING {len(tables)} TABLES FOR EDUCATION DATA ***") for i, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text().lower() # Check if table contains education and gender data has_education = any(term in table_text for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']) has_gender = any(term in table_text for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']) has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text)) if has_education and has_gender and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {i+1} CONTAINS EDUCATION + GENDER + STATISTICS ***") # Extract table structure rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f" Rows: {len(table_data)}") if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0]}") # Show first few data rows for j, row in enumerate(table_data[1:4]): if j + 1 < len(table_data): print(f" Row {j+1}: {row}") # Look for tertiary education specifically table_full_text = ' '.join([' '.join(row) for row in table_data]).lower() # Search for tertiary education patterns tertiary_patterns = [ 'tertiary', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω' ] found_tertiary = [pattern for pattern in tertiary_patterns if pattern in table_full_text] if found_tertiary: print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION INDICATORS: {found_tertiary} ***") # Try to extract specific numbers # Look for rows with gender and numbers for k, row in enumerate(table_data): row_text = ' '.join(row).lower() # Check if row contains gender terms and numbers has_men = any(term in row_text for term in ['men', 'male', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏']) has_women = any(term in row_text for term in ['women', 'female', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏']) numbers_in_row = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', ' '.join(row)) if (has_men or has_women) and numbers_in_row: print(f" *** POTENTIAL GENDER DATA ROW {k}: {row} ***") print(f" Numbers found: {numbers_in_row}") # Save this important table table_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{i}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{i}.json' table_info = { 'source_file': html_file, 'table_index': i, 'has_tertiary_education': bool(found_tertiary), 'tertiary_indicators': found_tertiary, 'row_count': len(table_data), 'table_data': table_data, 'extraction_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f" Table saved: {table_filename}") print(f" Data saved: {table_json_filename}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error analyzing HTML file: {e}") print() print("=== SUMMARY OF ANALYSIS ===\n") print(f"Workspace files analyzed: {len(all_files)}") print(f"JSON files inspected: {len(json_files)}") print(f"HTML files analyzed: {len(html_files)}") # Check if we found any tertiary education tables tertiary_tables = [f for f in os.listdir(workspace_path) if 'tertiary_education_gender_table' in f and f.endswith('.json')] if tertiary_tables: print(f"\n*** FOUND {len(tertiary_tables)} TABLES WITH TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") print("\nNext step: Extract specific numbers for men and women from these tables") else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education by gender data found.") print("May need to search for official NSI statistical publications or census reports.") print(f"\nAnalysis complete. Check workspace for extracted table files.")
