import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER - FIXED ANALYSIS ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Find gender-disaggregated statistics from 2011 Bulgarian census\n") # Check workspace for available files workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for census-related files...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) print(f"Found {len(all_files)} files in workspace:") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print() # Focus on HTML files that showed promise in previous analysis html_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f"HTML files for analysis: {len(html_files)}\n") # Target the most promising files based on previous output priority_html_files = [ 'nsi_education_source_7.html', # 42 tables, Bulgarian census indicators 'nsi_education_source_6.html', # 43 tables, Bulgarian census indicators 'www_nsi_bg_census2011_.html' # Official census site with education terms ] print("=== ANALYZING HIGH-PRIORITY HTML FILES FOR CENSUS TABLES ===\n") found_tertiary_tables = [] for html_file in priority_html_files: if html_file not in html_files: print(f"File not found: {html_file}") continue print(f"Analyzing: {html_file}") html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Get title title_element = soup.find('title') title_text = title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # Extract text content and convert to lowercase for analysis full_text = soup.get_text() text_content_lower = full_text.lower() # Check for Bulgarian census and education indicators census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'recensƒÉm√¢nt', '–ø—Ä–µ–±—Ä–æ—è–≤–∞–Ω–µ', 'population', '–Ω–∞—Å–µ–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ'] education_indicators = ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–ø–æ–ª'] found_census = [] for indicator in census_indicators: if indicator in text_content_lower: found_census.append(indicator) found_education = [] for indicator in education_indicators: if indicator in text_content_lower: found_education.append(indicator) found_gender = [] for indicator in gender_indicators: if indicator in text_content_lower: found_gender.append(indicator) print(f" Census indicators: {found_census}") print(f" Education indicators: {found_education}") print(f" Gender indicators: {found_gender}") # Look for tables tables = soup.find_all('table') print(f" Tables found: {len(tables)}") if tables and (found_education or found_gender): print(f" *** ANALYZING {len(tables)} TABLES FOR EDUCATION DATA ***") for table_index, table in enumerate(tables): # Extract table text and convert to lowercase table_text_content = table.get_text() table_text_lower = table_text_content.lower() # Check if table contains education and gender data has_education = False for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']: if term in table_text_lower: has_education = True break has_gender = False for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']: if term in table_text_lower: has_gender = True break has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text_content)) if has_education and has_gender and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {table_index+1} CONTAINS EDUCATION + GENDER + STATISTICS ***") # Extract table structure rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [] for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th']): cell_text = cell.get_text().strip() cells.append(cell_text) if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f" Rows: {len(table_data)}") if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0]}") # Show first few data rows for row_idx in range(1, min(4, len(table_data))): if row_idx < len(table_data): print(f" Row {row_idx}: {table_data[row_idx]}") # Look for tertiary education specifically table_full_text = '' for row in table_data: table_full_text += ' '.join(row) + ' ' table_full_text_lower = table_full_text.lower() # Search for tertiary education patterns tertiary_patterns = [ 'tertiary', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω' ] found_tertiary = [] for pattern in tertiary_patterns: if pattern in table_full_text_lower: found_tertiary.append(pattern) if found_tertiary: print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION INDICATORS: {found_tertiary} ***") # Try to extract specific numbers # Look for rows with gender and numbers for row_idx, row in enumerate(table_data): row_text = ' '.join(row) row_text_lower = row_text.lower() # Check if row contains gender terms and numbers has_men = False for term in ['men', 'male', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏']: if term in row_text_lower: has_men = True break has_women = False for term in ['women', 'female', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏']: if term in row_text_lower: has_women = True break numbers_in_row = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', row_text) if (has_men or has_women) and numbers_in_row: print(f" *** POTENTIAL GENDER DATA ROW {row_idx}: {row} ***") print(f" Numbers found: {numbers_in_row}") # This could be our target data! if has_men: print(f" -> MEN with tertiary education: {numbers_in_row}") if has_women: print(f" -> WOMEN with tertiary education: {numbers_in_row}") # Save this important table table_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{len(found_tertiary_tables)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{len(found_tertiary_tables)}.json' table_info = { 'source_file': html_file, 'table_index': table_index, 'has_tertiary_education': bool(found_tertiary), 'tertiary_indicators': found_tertiary, 'row_count': len(table_data), 'table_data': table_data, 'extraction_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) found_tertiary_tables.append(table_info) print(f" Table saved: {table_filename}") print(f" Data saved: {table_json_filename}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error analyzing HTML file: {e}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() print("=== SUMMARY OF ANALYSIS ===\n") print(f"Priority HTML files analyzed: {len(priority_html_files)}") print(f"Tables with tertiary education data found: {len(found_tertiary_tables)}") if found_tertiary_tables: print(f"\n*** FOUND {len(found_tertiary_tables)} TABLES WITH TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") for i, table_info in enumerate(found_tertiary_tables): print(f"\nTable {i+1}:") print(f" Source: {table_info['source_file']}") print(f" Tertiary indicators: {table_info['tertiary_indicators']}") print(f" Rows: {table_info['row_count']}") print(f" Data file: tertiary_education_gender_table_{i}.json") # Try to extract specific numbers from the table data table_data = table_info['table_data'] print(f" Sample data:") for j, row in enumerate(table_data[:5]): print(f" Row {j}: {row}") print(f"\nNext step: Examine the saved table files for specific men/women tertiary education numbers") else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education by gender data found.") print("May need to search for official NSI statistical publications or census reports.") print(f"\nAnalysis complete. Found {len(found_tertiary_tables)} relevant tables saved to workspace.")

Check workspace for available files workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for census-related files...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) print(f"Found {len(all_files)} files in workspace:") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print() # Focus on HTML files that showed promise in previous analysis html_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f"HTML files for analysis: {len(html_files)}\n") # Target the most promising files based on previous output priority_html_files = [ 'nsi_education_source_7.html', # 42 tables, Bulgarian census indicators 'nsi_education_source_6.html', # 43 tables, Bulgarian census indicators 'www_nsi_bg_census2011_.html' # Official census site with education terms ] print("=== ANALYZING HIGH-PRIORITY HTML FILES FOR CENSUS TABLES ===\n") found_tertiary_tables = [] for html_file in priority_html_files: if html_file not in html_files: print(f"File not found: {html_file}") continue print(f"Analyzing: {html_file}") html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Get title title_element = soup.find('title') title_text = title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title' print(f" Title: {title_text}") # Extract text content and convert to lowercase for analysis full_text = soup.get_text() text_content_lower = full_text.lower() # Check for Bulgarian census and education indicators census_indicators = ['2011', 'census', 'recensƒÉm√¢nt', '–ø—Ä–µ–±—Ä–æ—è–≤–∞–Ω–µ', 'population', '–Ω–∞—Å–µ–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ'] education_indicators = ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'gender', 'sex', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–ø–æ–ª'] found_census = [] for indicator in census_indicators: if indicator in text_content_lower: found_census.append(indicator) found_education = [] for indicator in education_indicators: if indicator in text_content_lower: found_education.append(indicator) found_gender = [] for indicator in gender_indicators: if indicator in text_content_lower: found_gender.append(indicator) print(f" Census indicators: {found_census}") print(f" Education indicators: {found_education}") print(f" Gender indicators: {found_gender}") # Look for tables tables = soup.find_all('table') print(f" Tables found: {len(tables)}") if tables and (found_education or found_gender): print(f" *** ANALYZING {len(tables)} TABLES FOR EDUCATION DATA ***") for table_index, table in enumerate(tables): # Extract table text and convert to lowercase table_text_content = table.get_text() table_text_lower = table_text_content.lower() # Check if table contains education and gender data has_education = False for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']: if term in table_text_lower: has_education = True break has_gender = False for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']: if term in table_text_lower: has_gender = True break has_numbers = bool(re.search(r'\d{3,}', table_text_content)) if has_education and has_gender and has_numbers: print(f"\n *** TABLE {table_index+1} CONTAINS EDUCATION + GENDER + STATISTICS ***") # Extract table structure rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [] for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th']): cell_text = cell.get_text().strip() cells.append(cell_text) if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f" Rows: {len(table_data)}") if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0]}") # Show first few data rows for row_idx in range(1, min(4, len(table_data))): if row_idx < len(table_data): print(f" Row {row_idx}: {table_data[row_idx]}") # Look for tertiary education specifically table_full_text = '' for row in table_data: table_full_text += ' '.join(row) + ' ' table_full_text_lower = table_full_text.lower() # Search for tertiary education patterns tertiary_patterns = [ 'tertiary', 'higher education', 'university degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω' ] found_tertiary = [] for pattern in tertiary_patterns: if pattern in table_full_text_lower: found_tertiary.append(pattern) if found_tertiary: print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION INDICATORS: {found_tertiary} ***") # Try to extract specific numbers # Look for rows with gender and numbers for row_idx, row in enumerate(table_data): row_text = ' '.join(row) row_text_lower = row_text.lower() # Check if row contains gender terms and numbers has_men = False for term in ['men', 'male', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏']: if term in row_text_lower: has_men = True break has_women = False for term in ['women', 'female', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏']: if term in row_text_lower: has_women = True break numbers_in_row = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', row_text) if (has_men or has_women) and numbers_in_row: print(f" *** POTENTIAL GENDER DATA ROW {row_idx}: {row} ***") print(f" Numbers found: {numbers_in_row}") # This could be our target data! if has_men: print(f" -> MEN with tertiary education: {numbers_in_row}") if has_women: print(f" -> WOMEN with tertiary education: {numbers_in_row}") # Save this important table table_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{len(found_tertiary_tables)}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) table_json_filename = f'workspace/tertiary_education_gender_table_{len(found_tertiary_tables)}.json' table_info = { 'source_file': html_file, 'table_index': table_index, 'has_tertiary_education': bool(found_tertiary), 'tertiary_indicators': found_tertiary, 'row_count': len(table_data), 'table_data': table_data, 'extraction_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } with open(table_json_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(table_info, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) found_tertiary_tables.append(table_info) print(f" Table saved: {table_filename}") print(f" Data saved: {table_json_filename}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error analyzing HTML file: {e}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() print() print("=== SUMMARY OF ANALYSIS ===\n") print(f"Priority HTML files analyzed: {len(priority_html_files)}") print(f"Tables with tertiary education data found: {len(found_tertiary_tables)}") if found_tertiary_tables: print(f"\n*** FOUND {len(found_tertiary_tables)} TABLES WITH TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") for i, table_info in enumerate(found_tertiary_tables): print(f"\nTable {i+1}:") print(f" Source: {table_info['source_file']}") print(f" Tertiary indicators: {table_info['tertiary_indicators']}") print(f" Rows: {table_info['row_count']}") print(f" Data file: tertiary_education_gender_table_{i}.json") # Try to extract specific numbers from the table data table_data = table_info['table_data'] print(f" Sample data:") for j, row in enumerate(table_data[:5]): print(f" Row {j}: {row}") print(f"\nNext step: Examine the saved table files for specific men/women tertiary education numbers") else: print("\nNo tables with clear tertiary education by gender data found.") print("May need to search for official NSI statistical publications or census reports.") print(f"\nAnalysis complete. Found {len(found_tertiary_tables)} relevant tables saved to workspace.")

import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TARGETED TERTIARY EDUCATION EXTRACTION ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Find gender-disaggregated statistics from 2011 Bulgarian census\n") # Check workspace for available files workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for census-related files...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) print(f"Found {len(all_files)} files in workspace:\n") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print() # First, let's inspect the PDF file which is likely to contain detailed census statistics pdf_file = 'nsi_education_source_4.pdf' if pdf_file in all_files: print(f"=== FOUND LARGE PDF FILE: {pdf_file} (1.2MB) ===\n") print("This is likely the official census report with detailed statistics.") print("PDF files typically contain the most comprehensive census data.\n") # Now let's focus on the HTML files that showed education indicators # Based on previous output, these files contain navigation menus with education links print("=== ANALYZING HTML FILES WITH EDUCATION LINKS ===\n") # Target files that showed education indicators in previous analysis target_files = [ 'nsi_education_source_7.html', # Had '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' indicator 'nsi_education_source_6.html', # Had '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' indicator 'www_nsi_bg_census2011_.html' # Official census site ] for html_file in target_files: if html_file not in all_files: print(f"File not found: {html_file}") continue print(f"Analyzing: {html_file}") html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Look for links that might lead to education statistics all_links = soup.find_all('a', href=True) education_links = [] for link in all_links: href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() # Check for education-related links education_keywords = ['–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', 'education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω'] gender_keywords = ['–ø–æ–ª', 'gender', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', 'men', 'women'] link_content = (href + ' ' + text).lower() has_education = any(keyword in link_content for keyword in education_keywords) has_gender = any(keyword in link_content for keyword in gender_keywords) if has_education or has_gender: education_links.append({ 'href': href, 'text': text, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender }) print(f" Found {len(education_links)} education/gender-related links:") for i, link in enumerate(education_links[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f" {i+1}. {link['text'][:50]}... -> {link['href'][:50]}...") if link['has_education']: print(f" *** EDUCATION LINK ***") if link['has_gender']: print(f" *** GENDER LINK ***") # Look for specific text patterns that might indicate tertiary education statistics full_text = soup.get_text() # Search for patterns like "higher education by gender" in Bulgarian education_patterns = [ r'–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ.*?–ø–æ–ª', r'–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ.*?–º—ä–∂–µ.*?–∂–µ–Ω–∏', r'—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ.*?–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', r'tertiary.*?education.*?gender', r'higher.*?education.*?sex', r'education.*?attainment.*?gender' ] found_patterns = [] for pattern in education_patterns: matches = re.findall(pattern, full_text.lower(), re.DOTALL) if matches: found_patterns.extend(matches) if found_patterns: print(f" *** FOUND EDUCATION PATTERNS: ***") for pattern in found_patterns[:5]: # Show first 5 print(f" - {pattern[:100]}...") # Look for numerical data that could be education statistics # Search for patterns like numbers followed by education terms number_education_patterns = [ r'(\d{1,3}[\s,]\d{3}|\d{4,}).*?(–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ|education)', r'(–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ|education).*?(\d{1,3}[\s,]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(–º—ä–∂–µ|–∂–µ–Ω–∏|men|women).*?(\d{1,3}[\s,]\d{3}|\d{4,}).*?(–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ|education)', ] statistical_matches = [] for pattern in number_education_patterns: matches = re.findall(pattern, full_text, re.IGNORECASE) statistical_matches.extend(matches) if statistical_matches: print(f" *** FOUND STATISTICAL PATTERNS: ***") for match in statistical_matches[:5]: # Show first 5 print(f" - {match}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error analyzing HTML file: {e}") print() # Now let's look for any table files that might have been saved from previous attempts print("=== CHECKING FOR SAVED TABLE FILES ===\n") table_files = [f for f in all_files if 'table' in f.lower()] if table_files: print(f"Found {len(table_files)} table files:") for table_file in table_files: print(f" - {table_file}") if table_file.endswith('.json'): # Inspect the table JSON file table_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, table_file) try: with open(table_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: table_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(table_content)} characters") # First inspect the structure try: table_data = json.loads(table_content) print(f" JSON type: {type(table_data)}") if isinstance(table_data, dict): print(f" Keys: {list(table_data.keys())}") # Look for table_data key which should contain the actual data if 'table_data' in table_data: actual_table = table_data['table_data'] print(f" Table has {len(actual_table)} rows") # Show sample rows for i, row in enumerate(actual_table[:3]): print(f" Row {i}: {row[:3] if len(row) > 3 else row}...") # Look for tertiary education data in the table table_text = json.dumps(actual_table).lower() tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏'] found_tertiary = [ind for ind in tertiary_indicators if ind in table_text] found_gender = [ind for ind in gender_indicators if ind in table_text] if found_tertiary and found_gender: print(f" *** TABLE CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION AND GENDER DATA ***") print(f" Tertiary indicators: {found_tertiary}") print(f" Gender indicators: {found_gender}") # Try to extract specific numbers for row_idx, row in enumerate(actual_table): row_text = ' '.join(str(cell) for cell in row).lower() # Look for rows with both gender and numbers has_gender_term = any(term in row_text for term in gender_indicators) has_numbers = re.search(r'\d{3,}', row_text) if has_gender_term and has_numbers: numbers = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', ' '.join(str(cell) for cell in row)) print(f" *** ROW {row_idx} - GENDER + NUMBERS: {row}") print(f" Numbers: {numbers}") except json.JSONDecodeError as e: print(f" JSON parsing error: {e}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error reading table file: {e}") print() else: print("No table files found from previous extractions.") # Let's try a different approach - look for census results pages directly print("=== SEARCHING FOR CENSUS RESULTS IN HTML CONTENT ===\n") # Look for files that might contain actual census data tables for html_file in all_files: if not html_file.endswith('.html'): continue html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() # Look for actual data tables with numbers soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') tables = soup.find_all('table') for table_idx, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text() # Look for tables with education levels and numerical data education_levels = ['primary', 'secondary', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤–Ω–æ', '—Å—Ä–µ–¥–Ω–æ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ'] has_education_levels = any(level in table_text.lower() for level in education_levels) has_large_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{4,}\b', table_text)) > 2 has_gender_columns = any(term in table_text.lower() for term in ['–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', 'male', 'female']) if has_education_levels and has_large_numbers and has_gender_columns: print(f"*** FOUND POTENTIAL EDUCATION STATISTICS TABLE in {html_file} ***") print(f"Table {table_idx + 1}:") # Extract table data rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f" Rows: {len(table_data)}") if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0]}") # Show rows that might contain tertiary education data for row_idx, row in enumerate(table_data[1:6]): # Show first 5 data rows row_text = ' '.join(row).lower() if any(term in row_text for term in ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']): print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION ROW {row_idx + 1}: {row} ***") # Extract numbers from this row numbers = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', ' '.join(row)) if numbers: print(f" Numbers found: {numbers}") # Try to identify which numbers correspond to men/women if len(numbers) >= 2: print(f" Potential gender breakdown:") print(f" Total or Men: {numbers[0]}") if len(numbers) > 1: print(f" Women or Second category: {numbers[1]}") if len(numbers) > 2: print(f" Additional categories: {numbers[2:]}") # Save this promising table table_filename = f'workspace/education_statistics_table_{html_file}_{table_idx}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) print(f" Table saved to: {table_filename}") print() except Exception as e: continue # Skip files that can't be processed print("=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print("Summary: Searched for tertiary education statistics by gender in Bulgarian census data.") print("Next steps: Examine any saved table files or access the PDF document for detailed statistics.")

import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: TARGETED TERTIARY EDUCATION EXTRACTION ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Find gender-disaggregated statistics from 2011 Bulgarian census\n") # Check workspace for available files workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for census-related files...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) print(f"Found {len(all_files)} files in workspace:\n") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print() # First, let's inspect the PDF file which is likely to contain detailed census statistics pdf_file = 'nsi_education_source_4.pdf' if pdf_file in all_files: print(f"=== FOUND LARGE PDF FILE: {pdf_file} (1.2MB) ===\n") print("This is likely the official census report with detailed statistics.") print("PDF files typically contain the most comprehensive census data.\n") # Now let's focus on the HTML files that showed education indicators # Based on previous output, these files contain navigation menus with education links print("=== ANALYZING HTML FILES WITH EDUCATION LINKS ===\n") # Target files that showed education indicators in previous analysis target_files = [ 'nsi_education_source_7.html', # Had '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' indicator 'nsi_education_source_6.html', # Had '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ' indicator 'www_nsi_bg_census2011_.html' # Official census site ] for html_file in target_files: if html_file not in all_files: print(f"File not found: {html_file}") continue print(f"Analyzing: {html_file}") html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(html_content)} characters") # Parse HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Look for links that might lead to education statistics all_links = soup.find_all('a', href=True) education_links = [] for link in all_links: href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() # Check for education-related links education_keywords = ['–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', 'education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω'] gender_keywords = ['–ø–æ–ª', 'gender', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', 'men', 'women'] link_content = (href + ' ' + text).lower() has_education = any(keyword in link_content for keyword in education_keywords) has_gender = any(keyword in link_content for keyword in gender_keywords) if has_education or has_gender: education_links.append({ 'href': href, 'text': text, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender }) print(f" Found {len(education_links)} education/gender-related links:") for i, link in enumerate(education_links[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f" {i+1}. {link['text'][:50]}... -> {link['href'][:50]}...") if link['has_education']: print(f" *** EDUCATION LINK ***") if link['has_gender']: print(f" *** GENDER LINK ***") # Look for specific text patterns that might indicate tertiary education statistics full_text = soup.get_text() # Search for patterns like "higher education by gender" in Bulgarian education_patterns = [ r'–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ.*?–ø–æ–ª', r'–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ.*?–º—ä–∂–µ.*?–∂–µ–Ω–∏', r'—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ.*?–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', r'tertiary.*?education.*?gender', r'higher.*?education.*?sex', r'education.*?attainment.*?gender' ] found_patterns = [] for pattern in education_patterns: matches = re.findall(pattern, full_text.lower(), re.DOTALL) if matches: found_patterns.extend(matches) if found_patterns: print(f" *** FOUND EDUCATION PATTERNS: ***") for pattern in found_patterns[:5]: # Show first 5 print(f" - {pattern[:100]}...") # Look for numerical data that could be education statistics # Search for patterns like numbers followed by education terms number_education_patterns = [ r'(\d{1,3}[\s,]\d{3}|\d{4,}).*?(–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ|education)', r'(–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ|education).*?(\d{1,3}[\s,]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(–º—ä–∂–µ|–∂–µ–Ω–∏|men|women).*?(\d{1,3}[\s,]\d{3}|\d{4,}).*?(–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ|education)', ] statistical_matches = [] for pattern in number_education_patterns: matches = re.findall(pattern, full_text, re.IGNORECASE) statistical_matches.extend(matches) if statistical_matches: print(f" *** FOUND STATISTICAL PATTERNS: ***") for match in statistical_matches[:5]: # Show first 5 print(f" - {match}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error analyzing HTML file: {e}") print() # Now let's look for any table files that might have been saved from previous attempts print("=== CHECKING FOR SAVED TABLE FILES ===\n") table_files = [f for f in all_files if 'table' in f.lower()] if table_files: print(f"Found {len(table_files)} table files:") for table_file in table_files: print(f" - {table_file}") if table_file.endswith('.json'): # Inspect the table JSON file table_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, table_file) try: with open(table_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: table_content = f.read() print(f" File size: {len(table_content)} characters") # First inspect the structure try: table_data = json.loads(table_content) print(f" JSON type: {type(table_data)}") if isinstance(table_data, dict): print(f" Keys: {list(table_data.keys())}") # Look for table_data key which should contain the actual data if 'table_data' in table_data: actual_table = table_data['table_data'] print(f" Table has {len(actual_table)} rows") # Show sample rows for i, row in enumerate(actual_table[:3]): print(f" Row {i}: {row[:3] if len(row) > 3 else row}...") # Look for tertiary education data in the table table_text = json.dumps(actual_table).lower() tertiary_indicators = ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', 'degree', 'bachelor', 'master', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ'] gender_indicators = ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏'] found_tertiary = [ind for ind in tertiary_indicators if ind in table_text] found_gender = [ind for ind in gender_indicators if ind in table_text] if found_tertiary and found_gender: print(f" *** TABLE CONTAINS TERTIARY EDUCATION AND GENDER DATA ***") print(f" Tertiary indicators: {found_tertiary}") print(f" Gender indicators: {found_gender}") # Try to extract specific numbers for row_idx, row in enumerate(actual_table): row_text = ' '.join(str(cell) for cell in row).lower() # Look for rows with both gender and numbers has_gender_term = any(term in row_text for term in gender_indicators) has_numbers = re.search(r'\d{3,}', row_text) if has_gender_term and has_numbers: numbers = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', ' '.join(str(cell) for cell in row)) print(f" *** ROW {row_idx} - GENDER + NUMBERS: {row}") print(f" Numbers: {numbers}") except json.JSONDecodeError as e: print(f" JSON parsing error: {e}") except Exception as e: print(f" Error reading table file: {e}") print() else: print("No table files found from previous extractions.") # Let's try a different approach - look for census results pages directly print("=== SEARCHING FOR CENSUS RESULTS IN HTML CONTENT ===\n") # Look for files that might contain actual census data tables for html_file in all_files: if not html_file.endswith('.html'): continue html_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, html_file) try: with open(html_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() # Look for actual data tables with numbers soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') tables = soup.find_all('table') for table_idx, table in enumerate(tables): table_text = table.get_text() # Look for tables with education levels and numerical data education_levels = ['primary', 'secondary', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤–Ω–æ', '—Å—Ä–µ–¥–Ω–æ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ'] has_education_levels = any(level in table_text.lower() for level in education_levels) has_large_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{4,}\b', table_text)) > 2 has_gender_columns = any(term in table_text.lower() for term in ['–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', 'male', 'female']) if has_education_levels and has_large_numbers and has_gender_columns: print(f"*** FOUND POTENTIAL EDUCATION STATISTICS TABLE in {html_file} ***") print(f"Table {table_idx + 1}:") # Extract table data rows = table.find_all('tr') table_data = [] for row in rows: cells = [cell.get_text().strip() for cell in row.find_all(['td', 'th'])] if cells: table_data.append(cells) print(f" Rows: {len(table_data)}") if table_data: print(f" Headers: {table_data[0]}") # Show rows that might contain tertiary education data for row_idx, row in enumerate(table_data[1:6]): # Show first 5 data rows row_text = ' '.join(row).lower() if any(term in row_text for term in ['tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']): print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION ROW {row_idx + 1}: {row} ***") # Extract numbers from this row numbers = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', ' '.join(row)) if numbers: print(f" Numbers found: {numbers}") # Try to identify which numbers correspond to men/women if len(numbers) >= 2: print(f" Potential gender breakdown:") print(f" Total or Men: {numbers[0]}") if len(numbers) > 1: print(f" Women or Second category: {numbers[1]}") if len(numbers) > 2: print(f" Additional categories: {numbers[2:]}") # Save this promising table table_filename = f'workspace/education_statistics_table_{html_file}_{table_idx}.html' with open(table_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(str(table)) print(f" Table saved to: {table_filename}") print() except Exception as e: continue # Skip files that can't be processed print("=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print("Summary: Searched for tertiary education statistics by gender in Bulgarian census data.") print("Next steps: Examine any saved table files or access the PDF document for detailed statistics.")

Python Code python
import os import json import subprocess import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: PDF EXTRACTION FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION STATISTICS ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Process the official NSI PDF census report for detailed statistics\n") # Check workspace for the PDF file workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for the PDF census report...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) pdf_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.pdf')] print(f"Found {len(pdf_files)} PDF files:") for pdf_file in pdf_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, pdf_file) file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {pdf_file} ({file_size} bytes)") if not pdf_files: print("No PDF files found. Checking all files in workspace:") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print("\nNo PDF files available for processing.") else: # Process the main PDF file (likely the census report) target_pdf = 'nsi_education_source_4.pdf' if target_pdf in pdf_files: print(f"\n=== PROCESSING MAIN CENSUS PDF: {target_pdf} ===\n") pdf_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, target_pdf) print(f"PDF file size: {os.path.getsize(pdf_path)} bytes (1.2MB)") print("This appears to be the official Bulgarian NSI census report.\n") # Try to extract text from PDF using pdftotext if available print("Attempting to extract text from PDF...") try: # Try using pdftotext command result = subprocess.run(['pdftotext', pdf_path, '-'], capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60) if result.returncode == 0 and result.stdout: pdf_text = result.stdout print(f"Successfully extracted text using pdftotext: {len(pdf_text)} characters") # Save extracted text for analysis text_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt') with open(text_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(pdf_text) print(f"Extracted text saved to: {text_filename}\n") else: print("pdftotext failed or returned empty result") pdf_text = None except FileNotFoundError: print("pdftotext command not found, trying alternative method...") pdf_text = None except subprocess.TimeoutExpired: print("pdftotext timed out") pdf_text = None except Exception as e: print(f"Error with pdftotext: {e}") pdf_text = None # If pdftotext didn't work, try using Python libraries if pdf_text is None: print("Trying Python PDF processing libraries...") try: import PyPDF2 with open(pdf_path, 'rb') as file: pdf_reader = PyPDF2.PdfReader(file) pdf_text = "" print(f"PDF has {len(pdf_reader.pages)} pages") for page_num, page in enumerate(pdf_reader.pages): try: page_text = page.extract_text() pdf_text += page_text + "\n" if page_num < 5: # Show progress for first few pages print(f" Extracted page {page_num + 1}: {len(page_text)} characters") except Exception as e: print(f" Error extracting page {page_num + 1}: {e}") if pdf_text.strip(): print(f"Successfully extracted text using PyPDF2: {len(pdf_text)} characters") # Save extracted text text_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt') with open(text_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(pdf_text) print(f"Extracted text saved to: {text_filename}\n") else: print("PyPDF2 extraction resulted in empty text") pdf_text = None except ImportError: print("PyPDF2 not available, trying pdfplumber...") try: import pdfplumber with pdfplumber.open(pdf_path) as pdf: pdf_text = "" print(f"PDF has {len(pdf.pages)} pages") for page_num, page in enumerate(pdf.pages): try: page_text = page.extract_text() if page_text: pdf_text += page_text + "\n" if page_num < 5: # Show progress for first few pages print(f" Extracted page {page_num + 1}: {len(page_text) if page_text else 0} characters") except Exception as e: print(f" Error extracting page {page_num + 1}: {e}") if pdf_text.strip(): print(f"Successfully extracted text using pdfplumber: {len(pdf_text)} characters") # Save extracted text text_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt') with open(text_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(pdf_text) print(f"Extracted text saved to: {text_filename}\n") else: print("pdfplumber extraction resulted in empty text") pdf_text = None except ImportError: print("pdfplumber not available either") pdf_text = None except Exception as e: print(f"Error with pdfplumber: {e}") pdf_text = None # If we successfully extracted text, analyze it for tertiary education statistics if pdf_text and pdf_text.strip(): print("=== ANALYZING EXTRACTED PDF TEXT FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ===\n") # Convert to lowercase for analysis pdf_text_lower = pdf_text.lower() # Search for education-related sections education_keywords = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–¥–∏–ø–ª–æ–º–∞', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate' ] gender_keywords = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'by sex', 'by gender', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' ] print("Searching for education and gender terms in PDF text...") found_education_terms = [] for term in education_keywords: if term in pdf_text_lower: found_education_terms.append(term) found_gender_terms = [] for term in gender_keywords: if term in pdf_text_lower: found_gender_terms.append(term) print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}\n") if found_education_terms and found_gender_terms: print("*** PDF CONTAINS BOTH EDUCATION AND GENDER TERMS ***\n") # Look for statistical tables or sections with numbers # Search for patterns that might indicate tertiary education statistics # Pattern 1: Look for sections with "tertiary" or "higher" education tertiary_patterns = [ r'tertiary education.*?\n.*?\n.*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'higher education.*?\n.*?\n.*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ.*?\n.*?\n.*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})' ] print("Searching for tertiary education statistics patterns...") for i, pattern in enumerate(tertiary_patterns): matches = re.findall(pattern, pdf_text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) if matches: print(f"Pattern {i+1} matches: {matches[:5]}") # Pattern 2: Look for gender-disaggregated education data gender_education_patterns = [ r'(men|male|–º—ä–∂–µ).*?(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(women|female|–∂–µ–Ω–∏).*?(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(men|male|–º—ä–∂–µ).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(women|female|–∂–µ–Ω–∏).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})' ] print("\nSearching for gender-education statistical patterns...") gender_stats = [] for i, pattern in enumerate(gender_education_patterns): matches = re.findall(pattern, pdf_text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) if matches: print(f"Gender-education pattern {i+1}: {matches[:3]}") gender_stats.extend(matches) # Pattern 3: Look for table-like structures with education levels print("\nSearching for table structures with education data...") # Split text into lines and look for tabular data lines = pdf_text.split('\n') potential_table_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_lower = line.lower() # Look for lines that might be table headers or data rows has_education = any(term in line_lower for term in ['education', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', 'tertiary', 'higher', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']) has_gender = any(term in line_lower for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']) has_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{3,}\b', line)) >= 2 if (has_education or has_gender) and has_numbers: potential_table_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line.strip(), 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'numbers': re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line) }) print(f"Found {len(potential_table_lines)} lines with education/gender data and numbers:") for i, table_line in enumerate(potential_table_lines[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f" Line {table_line['line_number']}: {table_line['content'][:100]}...") print(f" Numbers: {table_line['numbers']}") if table_line['has_education']: print(f" *** CONTAINS EDUCATION TERMS ***") if table_line['has_gender']: print(f" *** CONTAINS GENDER TERMS ***") print() # Save analysis results analysis_results = { 'pdf_file': target_pdf, 'extraction_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'text_length': len(pdf_text), 'education_terms_found': found_education_terms, 'gender_terms_found': found_gender_terms, 'potential_statistics_lines': potential_table_lines, 'analysis_status': 'PDF text extracted and analyzed for education statistics' } results_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_analysis_results.json') with open(results_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"Analysis results saved to: {results_filename}") else: print("PDF does not contain both education and gender terms.") print("This may not be the correct document for tertiary education statistics.") else: print("Failed to extract readable text from PDF.") print("The PDF may be image-based or encrypted.") else: print(f"Target PDF file '{target_pdf}' not found in workspace.") print(f"Available PDF files: {pdf_files}") print("\n=== PDF ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print("Summary: Attempted to extract and analyze tertiary education statistics by gender from Bulgarian census PDF.") print("If successful, check the saved text and analysis files for specific numbers.")

import os import json import subprocess import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: PDF EXTRACTION FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION STATISTICS ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Process the official NSI PDF census report for detailed statistics\n") # Check workspace for the PDF file workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for the PDF census report...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) pdf_files = [f for f in all_files if f.endswith('.pdf')] print(f"Found {len(pdf_files)} PDF files:") for pdf_file in pdf_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, pdf_file) file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {pdf_file} ({file_size} bytes)") if not pdf_files: print("No PDF files found. Checking all files in workspace:") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print("\nNo PDF files available for processing.") else: # Process the main PDF file (likely the census report) target_pdf = 'nsi_education_source_4.pdf' if target_pdf in pdf_files: print(f"\n=== PROCESSING MAIN CENSUS PDF: {target_pdf} ===\n") pdf_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, target_pdf) print(f"PDF file size: {os.path.getsize(pdf_path)} bytes (1.2MB)") print("This appears to be the official Bulgarian NSI census report.\n") # Try to extract text from PDF using pdftotext if available print("Attempting to extract text from PDF...") try: # Try using pdftotext command result = subprocess.run(['pdftotext', pdf_path, '-'], capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60) if result.returncode == 0 and result.stdout: pdf_text = result.stdout print(f"Successfully extracted text using pdftotext: {len(pdf_text)} characters") # Save extracted text for analysis text_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt') with open(text_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(pdf_text) print(f"Extracted text saved to: {text_filename}\n") else: print("pdftotext failed or returned empty result") pdf_text = None except FileNotFoundError: print("pdftotext command not found, trying alternative method...") pdf_text = None except subprocess.TimeoutExpired: print("pdftotext timed out") pdf_text = None except Exception as e: print(f"Error with pdftotext: {e}") pdf_text = None # If pdftotext didn't work, try using Python libraries if pdf_text is None: print("Trying Python PDF processing libraries...") try: import PyPDF2 with open(pdf_path, 'rb') as file: pdf_reader = PyPDF2.PdfReader(file) pdf_text = "" print(f"PDF has {len(pdf_reader.pages)} pages") for page_num, page in enumerate(pdf_reader.pages): try: page_text = page.extract_text() pdf_text += page_text + "\n" if page_num < 5: # Show progress for first few pages print(f" Extracted page {page_num + 1}: {len(page_text)} characters") except Exception as e: print(f" Error extracting page {page_num + 1}: {e}") if pdf_text.strip(): print(f"Successfully extracted text using PyPDF2: {len(pdf_text)} characters") # Save extracted text text_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt') with open(text_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(pdf_text) print(f"Extracted text saved to: {text_filename}\n") else: print("PyPDF2 extraction resulted in empty text") pdf_text = None except ImportError: print("PyPDF2 not available, trying pdfplumber...") try: import pdfplumber with pdfplumber.open(pdf_path) as pdf: pdf_text = "" print(f"PDF has {len(pdf.pages)} pages") for page_num, page in enumerate(pdf.pages): try: page_text = page.extract_text() if page_text: pdf_text += page_text + "\n" if page_num < 5: # Show progress for first few pages print(f" Extracted page {page_num + 1}: {len(page_text) if page_text else 0} characters") except Exception as e: print(f" Error extracting page {page_num + 1}: {e}") if pdf_text.strip(): print(f"Successfully extracted text using pdfplumber: {len(pdf_text)} characters") # Save extracted text text_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt') with open(text_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(pdf_text) print(f"Extracted text saved to: {text_filename}\n") else: print("pdfplumber extraction resulted in empty text") pdf_text = None except ImportError: print("pdfplumber not available either") pdf_text = None except Exception as e: print(f"Error with pdfplumber: {e}") pdf_text = None # If we successfully extracted text, analyze it for tertiary education statistics if pdf_text and pdf_text.strip(): print("=== ANALYZING EXTRACTED PDF TEXT FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ===\n") # Convert to lowercase for analysis pdf_text_lower = pdf_text.lower() # Search for education-related sections education_keywords = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–¥–∏–ø–ª–æ–º–∞', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate' ] gender_keywords = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'by sex', 'by gender', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' ] print("Searching for education and gender terms in PDF text...") found_education_terms = [] for term in education_keywords: if term in pdf_text_lower: found_education_terms.append(term) found_gender_terms = [] for term in gender_keywords: if term in pdf_text_lower: found_gender_terms.append(term) print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}\n") if found_education_terms and found_gender_terms: print("*** PDF CONTAINS BOTH EDUCATION AND GENDER TERMS ***\n") # Look for statistical tables or sections with numbers # Search for patterns that might indicate tertiary education statistics # Pattern 1: Look for sections with "tertiary" or "higher" education tertiary_patterns = [ r'tertiary education.*?\n.*?\n.*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'higher education.*?\n.*?\n.*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ.*?\n.*?\n.*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})' ] print("Searching for tertiary education statistics patterns...") for i, pattern in enumerate(tertiary_patterns): matches = re.findall(pattern, pdf_text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) if matches: print(f"Pattern {i+1} matches: {matches[:5]}") # Pattern 2: Look for gender-disaggregated education data gender_education_patterns = [ r'(men|male|–º—ä–∂–µ).*?(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(women|female|–∂–µ–Ω–∏).*?(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(men|male|–º—ä–∂–µ).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})', r'(education|–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ).*?(women|female|–∂–µ–Ω–∏).*?(\d{1,3}[,\s]\d{3}|\d{4,})' ] print("\nSearching for gender-education statistical patterns...") gender_stats = [] for i, pattern in enumerate(gender_education_patterns): matches = re.findall(pattern, pdf_text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) if matches: print(f"Gender-education pattern {i+1}: {matches[:3]}") gender_stats.extend(matches) # Pattern 3: Look for table-like structures with education levels print("\nSearching for table structures with education data...") # Split text into lines and look for tabular data lines = pdf_text.split('\n') potential_table_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_lower = line.lower() # Look for lines that might be table headers or data rows has_education = any(term in line_lower for term in ['education', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', 'tertiary', 'higher', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']) has_gender = any(term in line_lower for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']) has_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{3,}\b', line)) >= 2 if (has_education or has_gender) and has_numbers: potential_table_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line.strip(), 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'numbers': re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line) }) print(f"Found {len(potential_table_lines)} lines with education/gender data and numbers:") for i, table_line in enumerate(potential_table_lines[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f" Line {table_line['line_number']}: {table_line['content'][:100]}...") print(f" Numbers: {table_line['numbers']}") if table_line['has_education']: print(f" *** CONTAINS EDUCATION TERMS ***") if table_line['has_gender']: print(f" *** CONTAINS GENDER TERMS ***") print() # Save analysis results analysis_results = { 'pdf_file': target_pdf, 'extraction_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'text_length': len(pdf_text), 'education_terms_found': found_education_terms, 'gender_terms_found': found_gender_terms, 'potential_statistics_lines': potential_table_lines, 'analysis_status': 'PDF text extracted and analyzed for education statistics' } results_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'census_pdf_analysis_results.json') with open(results_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"Analysis results saved to: {results_filename}") else: print("PDF does not contain both education and gender terms.") print("This may not be the correct document for tertiary education statistics.") else: print("Failed to extract readable text from PDF.") print("The PDF may be image-based or encrypted.") else: print(f"Target PDF file '{target_pdf}' not found in workspace.") print(f"Available PDF files: {pdf_files}") print("\n=== PDF ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print("Summary: Attempted to extract and analyze tertiary education statistics by gender from Bulgarian census PDF.") print("If successful, check the saved text and analysis files for specific numbers.")

import os import json import re import time print("=== BULGARIAN CENSUS 2011: ANALYZING EXTRACTED PDF TEXT ===\n") print("Objective: Extract specific numbers for men and women with tertiary education completion") print("Target: Analyze the already extracted PDF text for detailed statistics\n") # Check workspace for extracted text file workspace_path = 'workspace' if not os.path.exists(workspace_path): os.makedirs(workspace_path) print("Created workspace directory") print("Checking workspace for extracted census text...") all_files = os.listdir(workspace_path) print(f"Found {len(all_files)} files in workspace:\n") for file in all_files: file_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size} bytes)") print() # Look for the extracted PDF text file text_file = 'census_pdf_extracted_text.txt' if text_file in all_files: print(f"=== FOUND EXTRACTED PDF TEXT: {text_file} ===\n") text_path = os.path.join(workspace_path, text_file) try: with open(text_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: pdf_text = f.read() print(f"Successfully loaded extracted text: {len(pdf_text)} characters") print(f"This is the text extracted from the 1.2MB Bulgarian census PDF\n") # Show first 500 characters to understand the content print("=== SAMPLE OF EXTRACTED TEXT ===\n") print(pdf_text[:500]) print("...\n") # Convert to lowercase for analysis pdf_text_lower = pdf_text.lower() # Search for education-related sections education_keywords = [ 'tertiary education', 'higher education', 'university', 'degree', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—É–Ω–∏–≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—Å–∫–æ –æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', '—Å—Ç–µ–ø–µ–Ω', '–¥–∏–ø–ª–æ–º–∞', 'bachelor', 'master', 'doctorate' ] gender_keywords = [ 'men', 'women', 'male', 'female', 'by sex', 'by gender', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', '–º—ä–∂–∫–∏', '–∂–µ–Ω—Å–∫–∏', '–ø–æ –ø–æ–ª' ] print("Searching for education and gender terms in PDF text...") found_education_terms = [] for term in education_keywords: if term in pdf_text_lower: found_education_terms.append(term) found_gender_terms = [] for term in gender_keywords: if term in pdf_text_lower: found_gender_terms.append(term) print(f"Education terms found: {found_education_terms}") print(f"Gender terms found: {found_gender_terms}\n") if found_education_terms and found_gender_terms: print("*** PDF CONTAINS BOTH EDUCATION AND GENDER TERMS ***\n") # Look for specific tertiary education sections print("=== SEARCHING FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION STATISTICS ===\n") # Split text into lines for analysis lines = pdf_text.split('\n') print(f"PDF text contains {len(lines)} lines") # Look for lines that contain tertiary education indicators tertiary_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_text = line.strip() line_text_lower = line_text.lower() # Check if line contains tertiary education terms has_tertiary = any(term in line_text_lower for term in ['tertiary', 'higher education', 'university', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']) if has_tertiary: tertiary_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line_text, 'numbers': re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line_text) }) print(f"Found {len(tertiary_lines)} lines with tertiary education indicators:") for i, tert_line in enumerate(tertiary_lines[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f"\nLine {tert_line['line_number']}: {tert_line['content']}") if tert_line['numbers']: print(f" Numbers found: {tert_line['numbers']}") # Look for gender-specific education data print("\n=== SEARCHING FOR GENDER-SPECIFIC EDUCATION DATA ===\n") gender_education_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_text = line.strip() line_text_lower = line_text.lower() # Check if line contains both education and gender terms has_education = any(term in line_text_lower for term in ['education', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university']) has_gender = any(term in line_text_lower for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']) has_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{3,}\b', line_text)) > 0 if has_education and has_gender and has_numbers: numbers_found = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line_text) gender_education_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line_text, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'numbers': numbers_found }) print(f"Found {len(gender_education_lines)} lines with education, gender, and numerical data:") for i, ge_line in enumerate(gender_education_lines[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f"\nLine {ge_line['line_number']}: {ge_line['content']}") print(f" Numbers: {ge_line['numbers']}") # Try to identify if this line contains our target data line_lower = ge_line['content'].lower() if 'tertiary' in line_lower or 'higher' in line_lower or 'university' in line_lower: print(f" *** POTENTIAL TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") # Check for men/women indicators if 'men' in line_lower and 'women' in line_lower: print(f" *** CONTAINS BOTH MEN AND WOMEN DATA ***") elif 'men' in line_lower or 'male' in line_lower: print(f" *** CONTAINS MEN DATA ***") elif 'women' in line_lower or 'female' in line_lower: print(f" *** CONTAINS WOMEN DATA ***") # Look for table-like structures with education data print("\n=== SEARCHING FOR TABLE STRUCTURES ===\n") # Look for consecutive lines that might form a table potential_tables = [] current_table = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_text = line.strip() # Check if line looks like a table row (has multiple numbers or specific formatting) has_multiple_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{3,}\b', line_text)) >= 2 has_education_term = any(term in line_text.lower() for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ']) if has_multiple_numbers or has_education_term: current_table.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line_text, 'numbers': re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line_text) }) else: if len(current_table) >= 2: # If we have at least 2 lines, it might be a table potential_tables.append(current_table) current_table = [] # Add the last table if it exists if len(current_table) >= 2: potential_tables.append(current_table) print(f"Found {len(potential_tables)} potential table structures") # Analyze each potential table for table_idx, table in enumerate(potential_tables[:5]): # Show first 5 tables print(f"\n*** POTENTIAL TABLE {table_idx + 1} ***") print(f"Lines {table[0]['line_number']} to {table[-1]['line_number']}:") table_has_education = False table_has_gender = False for row in table: print(f" {row['content']}") if row['numbers']: print(f" Numbers: {row['numbers']}") # Check table content row_lower = row['content'].lower() if any(term in row_lower for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ']): table_has_education = True if any(term in row_lower for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']): table_has_gender = True if table_has_education and table_has_gender: print(f" *** THIS TABLE CONTAINS BOTH EDUCATION AND GENDER DATA ***") # Try to extract specific tertiary education numbers for row in table: row_lower = row['content'].lower() if ('tertiary' in row_lower or 'higher' in row_lower or 'university' in row_lower) and row['numbers']: print(f" *** TERTIARY EDUCATION ROW: {row['content']} ***") print(f" Numbers: {row['numbers']}") # These could be our target numbers! if len(row['numbers']) >= 2: print(f" POTENTIAL ANSWER:") print(f" Men with tertiary education: {row['numbers'][0]}") print(f" Women with tertiary education: {row['numbers'][1]}") if len(row['numbers']) > 2: print(f" Additional data: {row['numbers'][2:]}") # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_results = { 'pdf_analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'text_length': len(pdf_text), 'total_lines': len(lines), 'education_terms_found': found_education_terms, 'gender_terms_found': found_gender_terms, 'tertiary_education_lines': len(tertiary_lines), 'gender_education_lines': len(gender_education_lines), 'potential_tables': len(potential_tables), 'detailed_tertiary_lines': tertiary_lines[:10], 'detailed_gender_education_lines': gender_education_lines[:10], 'analysis_status': 'Comprehensive analysis of extracted PDF text completed' } results_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'comprehensive_census_analysis.json') with open(results_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\nComprehensive analysis saved to: {results_filename}") else: print("PDF does not contain both education and gender terms.") print("This may not be the correct document for tertiary education statistics.") except Exception as e: print(f"Error reading extracted text file: {e}") import traceback traceback.print_exc() else: print(f"Extracted text file '{text_file}' not found in workspace.") print("Available files:") for file in all_files: print(f" - {file}") print("\nMay need to extract PDF text first.") print("\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===\n") print("Summary: Analyzed extracted PDF text for tertiary education statistics by gender.") print("Look for lines marked with '*** TERTIARY EDUCATION ROW ***' for potential answers.")

Look for specific tertiary education sections print("=== SEARCHING FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION STATISTICS ===\n") # Split text into lines for analysis lines = pdf_text.split('\n') print(f"PDF text contains {len(lines)} lines") # Look for lines that contain tertiary education indicators tertiary_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_text = line.strip() # Define line_text_lower properly within the loop line_text_lower = line_text.lower() # Check if line contains tertiary education terms has_tertiary = any(term in line_text_lower for term in ['tertiary', 'higher education', 'university', '–≤–∏—Å—à–µ']) if has_tertiary: numbers_found = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line_text) tertiary_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line_text, 'numbers': numbers_found }) print(f"Found {len(tertiary_lines)} lines with tertiary education indicators:") for i, tert_line in enumerate(tertiary_lines[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f"\nLine {tert_line['line_number']}: {tert_line['content']}") if tert_line['numbers']: print(f" Numbers found: {tert_line['numbers']}") # Look for gender-specific education data print("\n=== SEARCHING FOR GENDER-SPECIFIC EDUCATION DATA ===\n") gender_education_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_text = line.strip() # Define line_text_lower properly within the loop line_text_lower = line_text.lower() # Check if line contains both education and gender terms has_education = any(term in line_text_lower for term in ['education', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university']) has_gender = any(term in line_text_lower for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏']) has_numbers = len(re.findall(r'\b\d{3,}\b', line_text)) > 0 if has_education and has_gender and has_numbers: numbers_found = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line_text) gender_education_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line_text, 'has_education': has_education, 'has_gender': has_gender, 'numbers': numbers_found }) print(f"Found {len(gender_education_lines)} lines with education, gender, and numerical data:") for i, ge_line in enumerate(gender_education_lines[:10]): # Show first 10 print(f"\nLine {ge_line['line_number']}: {ge_line['content']}") print(f" Numbers: {ge_line['numbers']}") # Try to identify if this line contains our target data # Define line_lower properly within the loop line_lower = ge_line['content'].lower() if 'tertiary' in line_lower or 'higher' in line_lower or 'university' in line_lower: print(f" *** POTENTIAL TERTIARY EDUCATION DATA ***") # Check for men/women indicators if 'men' in line_lower and 'women' in line_lower: print(f" *** CONTAINS BOTH MEN AND WOMEN DATA ***") # This could be our answer! if len(ge_line['numbers']) >= 2: print(f" *** POTENTIAL ANSWER FOUND ***") print(f" Men with tertiary education: {ge_line['numbers'][0]}") print(f" Women with tertiary education: {ge_line['numbers'][1]}") elif 'men' in line_lower or 'male' in line_lower: print(f" *** CONTAINS MEN DATA ***") elif 'women' in line_lower or 'female' in line_lower: print(f" *** CONTAINS WOMEN DATA ***") # Look for specific patterns that might indicate table data print("\n=== SEARCHING FOR STATISTICAL TABLES ===\n") # Look for lines with multiple large numbers that could be statistical data statistical_lines = [] for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_text = line.strip() # Define line_text_lower properly within the loop line_text_lower = line_text.lower() # Look for lines with multiple numbers (potential table rows) numbers_in_line = re.findall(r'\b\d{1,3}(?:[,\s]\d{3})*\b|\b\d{4,}\b', line_text) # Filter for lines with at least 2 substantial numbers substantial_numbers = [num for num in numbers_in_line if len(num.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '')) >= 3] if len(substantial_numbers) >= 2: # Check if this line or nearby lines contain education terms context_lines = [] for context_offset in range(-2, 3): # Check 2 lines before and after context_line_num = line_num + context_offset if 0 <= context_line_num < len(lines): context_lines.append(lines[context_line_num].lower()) context_text = ' '.join(context_lines) has_education_context = any(term in context_text for term in ['education', 'tertiary', 'higher', 'university', '–æ–±—Ä–∞–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ']) has_gender_context = any(term in context_text for term in ['men', 'women', 'male', 'female', '–º—ä–∂–µ', '–∂–µ–Ω–∏', 'sex']) if has_education_context and has_gender_context: statistical_lines.append({ 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line_text, 'numbers': substantial_numbers, 'has_education_context': has_education_context, 'has_gender_context': has_gender_context }) print(f"Found {len(statistical_lines)} lines with statistical data in education/gender context:") for i, stat_line in enumerate(statistical_lines[:15]): # Show first 15 print(f"\nLine {stat_line['line_number']}: {stat_line['content']}") print(f" Numbers: {stat_line['numbers']}") # Check if this could be our target data if len(stat_line['numbers']) >= 2: print(f" *** POTENTIAL GENDER BREAKDOWN ***") print(f" First number (possibly men): {stat_line['numbers'][0]}") print(f" Second number (possibly women): {stat_line['numbers'][1]}") # Look at surrounding lines for context context_start = max(0, stat_line['line_number'] - 2) context_end = min(len(lines), stat_line['line_number'] + 3) print(f" Context (lines {context_start}-{context_end}):") for ctx_line_num in range(context_start, context_end): if ctx_line_num < len(lines): ctx_content = lines[ctx_line_num].strip() if ctx_content: marker = ">>> " if ctx_line_num == stat_line['line_number'] else " " print(f" {marker}Line {ctx_line_num}: {ctx_content[:80]}...") # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_results = { 'pdf_analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'text_length': len(pdf_text), 'total_lines': len(lines), 'education_terms_found': found_education_terms, 'gender_terms_found': found_gender_terms, 'tertiary_education_lines_count': len(tertiary_lines), 'gender_education_lines_count': len(gender_education_lines), 'statistical_lines_count': len(statistical_lines), 'detailed_tertiary_lines': tertiary_lines[:5], 'detailed_gender_education_lines': gender_education_lines[:5], 'detailed_statistical_lines': statistical_lines[:10], 'analysis_status': 'Comprehensive analysis completed successfully' } results_filename = os.path.join(workspace_path, 'final_census_analysis.json') with open(results_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\nComprehensive analysis saved to: {results_filename}") # Summary of findings print("\n=== ANALYSIS SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total lines analyzed: {len(lines)}") print(f"Lines with tertiary education terms: {len(tertiary_lines)}") print(f"Lines with education + gender + numbers: {len(gender_education_lines)}") print(f"Lines with statistical data in education context: {len(statistical_lines)}") if statistical_lines: print("\n*** MOST PROMISING STATISTICAL LINES FOR TERTIARY EDUCATION BY GENDER: ***") for i, line in enumerate(statistical_lines[:3]): print(f"\n{i+1}.
